Vietnamese and their spouses and children who have been granted with certificate of visa exemption.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://news.chinhphu.vn/Home/BREAKING-VN-to-halt-entry-to-all-foreigners-since-March-22-due-to-COVID19/20203/39326.vgp |title = VGP News &#124; VN HALTS entry to all foreigners due to COVID-19 - VN HALTS entry to all foreigners due to COVID-19}}</ref>\n\n=== Africa ===\n*{{flag|Algeria}}: All international flights to Algeria are suspended.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/4218 | title=Algeria - restriction update 17.04.2020 11:46 UTC: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Cape Verde}}: On 17 March, as a contingency measure, Prime Minister [[Jos\u00e9 Ulisses Correia e Silva]] announced<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/travel/article/coronavirus-travel-bans/index.html |title=Coronavirus: Which countries have travel bans?|work=CNN |last=O'Hare |first=Maureen |last2=Hardingham |first2=Tamara |last-author-amp=y |date=17 March 2020 |accessdate=17 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.governo.cv/covid19-governo-declara-situacao-de-contingencia-a-nivel-da-protecao-civil/ |title=COVID19: Governo declara situa\u00e7\u00e3o de conting\u00eancia a n\u00edvel da Prote\u00e7\u00e3o Civil |publisher=Governo de Cabo Verde |language=Portuguese |date=17 March 2020 |access-date=20 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rtc.cv/tcv/index.php?paginas=47&id_cod=89239 |work=TCV |title=Governo declara situa\u00e7\u00e3o de conting\u00eancia, a n\u00edvel de Prote\u00e7\u00e3o Civil, por causa do Covid-19 |language=Portuguese |date=17 March 2020 |access-date=20 March 2020}}</ref> the suspension of all incoming flights from the [[United States|US]], [[Brazil]], [[Senegal]], [[Nigeria]], [[Portugal]], and all [[Europe]]an countries affected by the coronavirus. Since at the time Cape Verde had no air travel connections to other countries, in practice, this results in a lockdown.\n* {{flag|Democratic Republic of the Congo}}: The DRC government has declared a State of Emergency effective March 24 to limit the spread of COVID-19. All international passenger flights are suspended (except for limited special commercial flights, organized by embassies). All domestic passenger flights, as well as road and river transport, between Kinshasa and the provinces are suspended. Goods transport continues with controlled checkpoints.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cd.usembassy.gov/health-alert-u-s-embassy-kinshasa-democratic-republic-of-the-congo-9/|title=Health Alert: U.S. Embassy Kinshasa, Democratic Republic of the Congo|date=April 5, 2020}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Egypt}}: Egypt's Prime Minister Moustafa Madbouly announced that Egypt will be shutting down its airports and air travel starting from Thursday March 19 at noon until April 15 to prevent the spread of the coronavirus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://egyptianstreets.com/2020/03/16/egypt-shuts-down-airports-suspends-air-travel-pm/|title=Egypt Shuts Down Airports, Suspends Air Travel: PM|date=March 16, 2020}}</ref>\n* {{flag|The Gambia}}: Closed its sole land border with [[Senegal]], and closed its airspace to most flights.<ref>{{cite news |title=COVID-19: Gambia, Senegal to close border for 21 days |url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/africa/covid-19-gambia-senegal-to-close-border-for-21-days/1776298 |accessdate=1 April 2020}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Ghana}}: Effective March 17, 2020 Ghana will ban anyone that has been to a country with more than 200 cases in the previous 14 days, unless they are an official resident or a Ghanaian national. Citizens and resident-permit holders will be required to self-isolate for 14 days on arrival.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-03-15/ghana-closes-borders-for-arrivals-from-coronavirus-hit-countries |title=Africa Virus News, Ghana Latest: Borders Close For Some |publisher=Bloomberg |date=2020-03-15 |accessdate=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Kenya}}: Effective March 17, 2020 Kenya halted the entry of foreigners from countries that have confirmed coronavirus cases. Only Kenyan citizens, and any foreigners with valid residence permits will be allowed to come in provided they proceed on self-quarantine or to a government designated quarantine facility.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-03-15/kenya-restricts-foreign-travel-suspends-school-on-coronavirus |title=Africa, Kenya, Coronavirus News: Travel, Schools Hit by Virus Ban |publisher=Bloomberg |date=2020-03-15 |accessdate=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Madagascar}}: All flights to Madagascar are suspended until 20 April 2020.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3609 | title=Madagascar - restriction update 01.04.2020 12:24 UTC: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Mauritius}}: Passengers are not allowed to transit or enter Mauritius.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3615 | title=Mauritius - restriction update 01.04.2020 21:44 UTC: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Morocco}}: On March 15, 2020 Morocco suspended all international passenger flights to and from the country.<ref>{{cite web|author=Kirsten Donovan|date=March 15, 2020|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-morocco-flights/morocco-suspends-all-international-passenger-flights-foreign-ministry-idUSKBN2120QQ|title=Morocco suspends all international passenger flights - foreign ministry|trans-title=|language=en|website=reuters.com}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Namibia}}: Namibia's borders are closed until 23 April 2020.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/4217 | title=Namibia - restriction update 17.04.2020 08:30 UTC: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Nigeria}}: On March 26, 2020 Nigeria ordered the immediate closure of international airports and land borders for a period of four weeks.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vanguardngr.com/2020/03/breaking-buhari-directs-closure-of-air-land-borders-for-4-weeks|title=BREAKING: Buhari directs closure of air, land borders for 4 weeks|last=Ogunyinka|first=Victor|date=26 March 2020|accessdate=26 March 2020|publisher=[[Vanguard (Nigeria)|Vanguard Newspaper]]}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Seychelles}}: Effective 30 March 2020, Passengers are not allowed to enter Seychelles except specified categories of passengers.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3539 | title=Seychelles - restriction update 30.03.2020 08:10 UTC: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n* {{flag|South Africa}}: Ban on entry to all including South African citizens. This decision was made hours before lockdown officially began on 26 March at midnight. The Minister of Transport, Fikile Mbalula had hastily made the decision leaving over 3000 South African citizens stranded in foreign countries across the globe without support. It also left 6000 tourists within South Africa's borders stranded with no way to go home. After two weeks, plans were made to get the 6000 tourists home but no plans have been made for the 80 percent of South Africans left stranded. Three repatriation missions from Brazil, Germany and Botswana have been made as those yielded political points with the respective governments. \n* {{flag|Sudan}}: Effective March 17, 2020 Sudan declared a state of emergency and closed all airports and land borders, this after one person died of COVID-19 in the country.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.europapress.es/internacional/noticia-sudan-declara-estado-emergencia-sanitaria-cierra-puertos-aeropuertos-cruces-fronterizos-coronavirus-20200316193257.html|title=Sud\u00e1n declara el \"estado de emergencia sanitaria\" y cierra puertos, aeropuertos y cruces fronterizos por el coronavirus|first=Europa|last=Press|date=March 16, 2020|website=www.europapress.es}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Tunisia}}: All flights to Tunisia are suspended until 19 April 2020.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/4089 | title=Tunisia - restriction update 09.04.2020 13:14 UTC: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n\n===Americas===\n*{{flag|Argentina}}: Borders closed to non-residents, effective March 15.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.batimes.com.ar/news/argentina/argentina-to-close-schools-for-two-weeks-borders-to-visitors.phtml|title=Buenos Aires Times &#124; Argentina to close schools for two weeks, borders to visitors|website=www.batimes.com.ar}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Belize}}: Borders closed to all travellers, including Belizean nationals except for emergency situations.<ref>{{cite news |title=All borders closed to the entry of Belizean nationals |url=https://www.breakingbelizenews.com/2020/04/05/all-borders-closed-to-the-entry-of-belizean-nationals/ |accessdate=6 April 2020 |work=Breaking Belize News-The Leading Online News Source of Belize |date=5 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Belize is now on war footing; PM Barrow announces closure of borders to national |url=https://www.breakingbelizenews.com/2020/04/03/belize-is-now-on-war-footing-pm-barrow-announces-closure-of-borders-to-national/ |accessdate=6 April 2020 |work=Breaking Belize News-The Leading Online News Source of Belize |date=3 April 2020}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Bermuda}}: Effective March 20, 2020, a travel ban will be in place to disallow travellers to Bermuda unless the person is a Bermuda resident, a crew member, or a person with the written permission of the Quarantine Authority of Bermuda to enter.<ref>{{Citation | url = https://www.gov.bm/coronavirus | title = Novel Coronavirus (COVID-19) - Information for Travellers | date = 10 March 2020 | publisher = Govenment of Bermuda | accessdate = 2020-03-20}}</ref> Flights to Bermuda are suspended until 1 May 2020.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3740 | title=Bermuda - restriction update 02.04.2020 20:50 UTC: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Bolivia}}: Effective March 20, Borders closed to foreigners and international flights cancelled.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lostiempos.com/actualidad/pais/20200317/bolivia-cierra-fronteras-suspende-vuelos-limita-transporte-terrestre|title=Bolivia cierra fronteras, suspende vuelos y limita el transporte terrestre por el coronavirus|date=March 17, 2020|website=Los Tiempos}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Brazil}}: Effective March 30, 2020, passengers are not allowed to enter Brazil except specific categories of passengers.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3536 | title=Brazil - restrictions update 30.03.2020: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Canada}}: Borders are closed to all travellers who are not citizens, permanent residents or U.S. citizens. Exceptions are placed for diplomats, crew and immediate family members of citizens with clearing a basic health assessment by air operators.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/politics/cbsa-border-airports-screening-trudeau-covid19-coronavirus-1.5498866 |title = Canada to bar entry to travellers who are not citizens, permanent residents or Americans | work = CBC News | date = March 16, 2020 | accessdate = March 20, 2020}}</ref> The U.S. and Canada later agreed to close the [[Canada\u2013United States border]] to non-essential traffic.<ref>{{Cite news | url = https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-03-18/trump-says-u-s-canada-close-their-border-after-virus-spreads | title = U.S., Canada Agree to Block Leisure Travel Between the Countries | work = [[Bloomberg News]] | date = March 18, 2020 | accessdate = March 18, 2020}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Chile}}: Passengers are not allowed to enter Chile.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3891 | title=Chile - restriction update 04.04.2020 00:36 UTC: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Costa Rica}}: Borders closed to non-residents, effective March 16 through April 12. Exceptions in place for crews. All returning nationals and residents are subject to mandatory 14 day quarantine.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nacion.com/el-pais/salud/nuevo-coronavirus-en-costa-rica-gobierno-decreta/FWLVLR5NSZDZ3FKVHHWXYQSCHI/story/|title=Nuevo coronavirus en Costa Rica: Gobierno decreta estado de emergencia nacional|website=La Naci\u00f3n, Grupo Naci\u00f3n}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Colombia}}: Effective 17 March, Colombia will close borders completely until May 30. Cargo will be permitted, but no persons will be allowed to enter or exit.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.portafolio.co/economia/gobierno/colombia-cierra-sus-fronteras-539113|title=Colombia cierra sus fronteras durante los pr\u00f3ximos 75 d\u00edas|date=March 16, 2020|via=www.portfolio.co}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Cuba}}: Effective March 24, 2020, Borders closed to all non-residents; only Cuban and foreign residents will be allowed to enter the country.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://adncuba.com/noticias-de-cuba/cuba-anuncia-cierre-de-frontera-solo-podran-entrar-cubanos-y-extranjeros |title = Cuba anuncia cierre de frontera: Solo podr\u00e1n entrar cubanos y extranjeros residentes}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-cuba-president/cuba-bars-entry-to-foreign-tourists-in-bid-to-contain-coronavirus-spread-idUSKBN2173NC|title=Cuba bars entry to foreign tourists in bid to contain coronavirus spread|newspaper=Reuters|date=March 20, 2020|accessdate = March 21, 2020 |via=www.reuters.com}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Dominica}}: Suspended all flights.<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus: Travel restrictions, border shutdowns by country |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/coronavirus-travel-restrictions-border-shutdowns-country-200318091505922.html |accessdate=1 April 2020 |work=www.aljazeera.com}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Dominican Republic}}: The President of the Dominican Republic ordered to close all borders, effective March 19.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nydailynews.com/news/politics/ny-dominican-coronavirus-20200318-fedw3a473zcz5jkwh5d2xco4um-story.html|title=Dominican Republic closes borders over coronavirus, halts all incoming flights|date=March 18, 2020|via=www.nydailynews.com}}</ref> Flights to Dominican Rep. are suspended until 12 April 2020.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3594 | title=Dominican Republic - restriction update 31.03.2020 15:56 UTC: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Ecuador}}: Effective 25 March 2020, Ecuador's borders are closed, flights to Ecuador are suspended until 5 April 2020.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/tr/country/ec/ | title=Travel restrictions of Ecuador: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3196 | title=Travel restrictions update for Ecuador - 25.03.2020: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n*{{flag|El Salvador}}: On March 11, the President of El Salvador announced an Executive Order barring the entry of foreigners.<ref name=\"elsalvador.1\">{{cite web|url=https://sv.usembassy.gov/health-alert-u-s-embassy-san-salvador-el-salvador-march-12-2020/|title=Health Alert \u2013 U.S. Embassy San Salvador, El Salvador &#124; U.S. Embassy in El Salvador|date=March 12, 2020|website=U.S. Embassy in El Salvador}}</ref> The General Directorate of Migration will deny entry to all foreigners, excluding accredited diplomats and legal residents of El Salvador.<ref name=\"elsalvador.1\" />\n*{{flag|Guatemala}}: The Guatemalan Government announced on March 16 that the country was closing its borders for two weeks, starting on midnight March 17.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/article/coronavirus-travel-restrictions.html|title=Coronavirus Travel Restrictions, Across the Globe|website=The New York Times|accessdate=March 17, 2020}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Guyana}}: Airports in Guyana are closed to all international passenger flights until 1 May 2020.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3893 | title=Guyana - restriction update 04.04.2020 11:22 UTC: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Honduras}}: Borders closed to all traffic, aside from the movement of goods, effective March 15, 23:59.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hn.usembassy.gov/covid-19-information/|title=COVID-19 Information|date=March 26, 2020|website=U.S. Embassy in Honduras}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Jamaica}}: No entry except by government authorization.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\">{{cite web|url=https://www.iatatravelcentre.com/international-travel-document-news/1580226297.htm|title=IATA - International Travel Document News|website=www.iatatravelcentre.com}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Panama}}: From 11.59 p.m on Monday night (March 16), only Panamanians and foreign residents would be allowed to enter Panama.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.garda.com/crisis24/news-alerts/323071/panama-authorities-prohibit-all-foreigners-from-entering-the-country-due-to-covid-19-march-16-update-3 |title=Panama: Authorities prohibit all foreigners from entering the country due to COVID-19 March 16 /update 3 |publisher=Garda.com |date=2020-03-16 |accessdate=2020-03-30}}</ref> From 11.59 pm on Sunday 22 March, all international flights will be halted.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/foreign-travel-advice/panama/coronavirus|title=Foreign travel advice: Panama|last=|first=|date=2020|website=gov.uk|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=March 26, 2020}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Paraguay}}: Flights to Paraguay are suspended until 26 April 2020.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/4225 | title=Paraguay - restriction update 17.04.2020 18:12 UTC: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Peru}}: Peru restricts access to the interior of the country from 12:00 on March 17.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gestion.pe/peru/coronavirus-en-peru-presidente-martin-vizcarra-anuncia-cierre-de-todas-las-fronteras-durante-estado-de-emergencia-nndc-noticia/|title=Per\u00fa anuncia el cierre de todas sus fronteras para evitar el avance de coronavirus: Vigente desde el martes|first=Redacci\u00f3n|last=Gesti\u00f3n|date=March 16, 2020|website=Gesti\u00f3n}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Suriname}}: Will close its borders for all persons and flights starting March 14.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-suriname-confirmed/suriname-confirms-first-coronavirus-case-authorities-will-close-borders-idUSKBN210373 |title=Suriname confirms first coronavirus case, authorities will close borders |date=13 March 2020 |work=Reuters |access-date=13 March 2020 |via=www.reuters.com}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Trinidad and Tobago}}: On March 16, Trinidad and Tobago announced that it closed its borders to all except Trinidad and Tobago nationals and certain medical personnel,<ref>{{Cite news|last=Nanton|first=Sampson|url=http://www.guardian.co.tt/news/tt-shuts-down-borders-bars-to-be-closed-6.2.1080079.6b07bec899|title=T&T shuts down borders, bars to be closed|date=2020-03-16|work=Trinidad and Tobago Guardian|access-date=2020-03-16|url-status=live}}</ref> by midnight on March 17.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Clyne|first=Kalifa Sarah|url=https://newsday.co.tt/2020/03/16/government-shuts-tt-borders/|title=Government shuts TT borders|date=2020-03-16|work=Trinidad and Tobago Newsday|access-date=2020-03-16|url-status=live}}</ref> Airports in Trinidad and Tobago are closed until 30 April 2020.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3541 | title=Trinidad and Tobago - restriction update 30.03.2020 09:18 UTC: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Uruguay}} Borders closed to non-residents, effective April 1. <ref>{{cite news |title=Cierre total de fronteras para extranjeros, salvo en ciudades de frontera con Brasil |url=https://www.subrayado.com.uy/uruguay-resuelve-el-cierre-absoluto-fronteras-extranjeros-ciudades-fronterizas-brasil-n614022 |accessdate=5 April 2020 |work=subrayado.com.uy |language=es-ES}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Venezuela}}: Effective 10 April 2020, flights to Venezuela are suspended.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/4100 | title=Venezuela - restriction update 09.04.2020 22:48 UTC: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n\n=== Europe ===\n* {{flag|European Union}}: The European Council agreed on March 17 to ban incoming travel other than citizens from countries in the [[European Union]], [[European Economic Area]], Switzerland and United Kingdom, [[Long-term resident (European Union)|long-term residents]] and people with long-term visa or residence permits, family members of EU and EEA citizens, medical personnel and people responsible for transport of goods for 30 days.<ref name=\"schengen\" /><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.politico.eu/article/the-eu-european-union-coronavirus-covid19-travel-ban-explained/ |title = The EU travel ban explained|date = 17 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.europapress.es/internacional/noticia-lideres-europeos-aceptan-cerrar-fronteras-exteriores-ue-viajes-esenciales-20200317203959.html|title=Los l\u00edderes europeos aceptan cerrar las fronteras exteriores de la UE salvo para viajes \"esenciales\"|first=Europa|last=Press|date=March 17, 2020|website=www.europapress.es}}</ref> Each country has to implement the decision on the national level. Ireland choose to opt out from the decision due to the [[Common Travel Area]]. The agreement was to close borders for 30 days starting at noon on March 17, though enforcement did not begin immediately as planned.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.schengenvisainfo.com/news/breaking-eu-decides-to-close-all-schengen-borders-for-30-days/|title=BREAKING: EU Decides to Close All Schengen Borders For 30 Days|date=March 17, 2020|website=Schengen Visa Info}}</ref> By the end of March, all EU member states (except Ireland) and all associated Schengen states (Iceland, Liechtenstein, Norway and Switzerland) had introduced the travel restriction.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/PDF/?uri=CELEX:52020XC0330(02) |title=COVID-19: Guidance on the implementation of the temporary restriction on non-essential travel to the EU, on the facilitation of transit arrangements for the repatriation of EU citizens, and on the effects on visa policy |publisher=Official Journal of the European Union |date=30 March 2020}}</ref> Some member states went even further and also prohibited EU and EEA citizens from entering, unless they are permanently living in the country or transiting to their home country, which is generally still possible (see also section Non-global restrictions below):\n**{{flag|Austria}}: Closed land borders for persons not having medical certificate confirming negative test for SARS-CoV-2 within last four days. Visitors arriving by air without proof of recently testing negative will be allowed into the country, but placed in mandatory quarantine for 14 days or until they test negative.<ref>{{cite web |title=Grenzkontrollma\u00dfnahmen an \u00d6sterreichs Grenzen |url=https://bmi.gv.at/news.aspx?id=314A5A707A4547684D55733D |website=bmi.gv.at |accessdate=2 April 2020 |language=de}}</ref>\n**{{flag|Belgium}}: Closed its borders to non-essential travel on March 20.<ref>{{cite web |title=Belgian borders shut to non-essential travel |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/world/belgian-borders-shut-to-non-essential-travel-12562392 |website=CNA |accessdate=2 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n**{{flag|Croatia}}: Closed its borders to non-citizens on March 19.<ref>{{cite web |title=Croatia imposes new restrictions concerning cross-border traffic |url=https://www.croatiaweek.com/croatia-imposes-new-restrictions-concerning-cross-border-traffic/ |website=Croatia Week |accessdate=5 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n**{{flag|Czech Republic}}: Partially closed its borders on March 14. Closed its borders to all non-residents on March 16.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_the_Czech_Republic&oldid=945894827|title=2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Czech Republic|date=March 16, 2020|via=Wikipedia}}</ref>\n**{{flag|Denmark}}: Closed its borders to all non-citizens March 14.<ref name=\"denmark.1\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/health-coronavirus-denmark-idUSL8N2B673O|title=Denmark shutting its borders to curb spread of coronavirus, prime minister says|newspaper=Reuters|date=March 13, 2020|via=www.reuters.com}}</ref>  This includes a ban on crossing the border for all tourism, but exempts travellers with \"credible purpose\" such as non-citizen Danish residents.<ref name=\"denmark.1\" />\n**{{flag|Estonia}}: Effective March 17, 2020, foreign travellers are not allowed to enter. Right of entry will remain for citizens and those with a right of residence, and foreign citizens whose next of kin live in Estonia. Transit is allowed for foreigners not showing signs of the coronavirus. A mandatory two-week quarantine will be set for anyone entering the country.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.err.ee/1064173/estonia-to-close-borders-to-foreign-nationals-from-march-17|title=Estonia to close borders to foreign nationals from March 17|date=March 15, 2020|website=ERR}}</ref>\n**{{flag|Finland}}: Closed its borders on March 19, 2020, except for Finnish citizens returning to Finland, foreigners returning to their countries of origin, essential work-related travel, and goods. Finnish citizens returning home are recommended to quarantine themselves for 14 days after arrival.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://yle.fi/uutiset/3-11262175|title=Muutokset astuvat voimaan: Koronaviruksen aiheuttama poikkeustila sulkee koulut t\u00e4n\u00e4\u00e4n, rajat kiinni torstaina|date=March 18, 2020|website=Yle|access-date=March 20, 2020|language=fi}}</ref>\n**{{flag|Hungary}}: Hungary closed its borders for all passenger transport on March 17 and only Hungarian citizens and permanent residents from the EEA are allowed to enter.<ref>{{cite web |title=Borders Closed: Who Can Enter Hungary and How? |url=https://hungarytoday.hu/borders-closed-who-can-enter-hungary-and-how/ |website=Hungary Today |accessdate=5 April 2020 |language=en |date=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n**{{flag|Latvia}}: Effective March 17, 2020 all international passenger connections by air, railway, sea and road, were to be cancelled. Only Latvians and foreigners with residency rights in Latvia will be able to enter the country from outside the Schengen Area,<ref>{{cite web |title=Emergency situation in Latvia to restrict the spread of Covid-19 |url=https://www.mfa.gov.lv/en/consular-information/news/65754-emergency-situation-declared-throughout-the-national-territory-until-14-april-2020-to-restrict-the-spread-of-covid-19 |publisher=[[Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Republic of Latvia]] |accessdate=27 March 2020 |date=17 March 2020}}</ref> but entry of foreign citizens by private vehicle from other Schengen member countries was still allowed.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://eng.lsm.lv/article/society/health/latvia-to-close-borders-to-passenger-traffic-on-tuesday-17-march.a351774/ |title=Latvia to close borders to passenger traffic on Tuesday 17 March |date=14 March 2020 |publisher=[[Public Broadcasting of Latvia]] |access-date=27 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n**{{flag|Lithuania}}: Closed the border for foreigners, except for those with residence permits, effective 00:00 (UTC+02:00) March 16 \u2013 April 27, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lrv.lt/lt/naujienos/vyriausybe-nusprende-karantinas-tesiamas-iki-balandzio-13-dienos|title=Vyriausyb\u0117 nusprend\u0117: karantinas t\u0119siamas iki baland\u017eio 13 dienos|date=2020-03-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://lrv.lt/lt/naujienos/karantinas-pratestas-dar-dviem-savaitems-velyku-savaitgaliui-grieztesni-apribojimai|title=Karantinas prat\u0119stas dar dviem savait\u0117ms, Velyk\u0173 savaitgaliui \u2013 grie\u017etesni apribojimai|date=2020-04-08|publisher=[[Government of Lithuania|lrv.lt]]}}</ref>\n**{{flag|Poland}}: Effective March 15 \u2013 May 3, 2020,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gazetaprawna.pl/artykuly/1468355,premier-do-3-maja-zgodnie-z-prawem-miedzynarodowym-zamkniete-beda-granice.html|title=Premier: Do 3 maja zgodnie z prawem mi\u0119dzynarodowym zamkni\u0119te b\u0119d\u0105 granice|website=www.gazetaprawna.pl|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref> entry ban for all foreigners except for those with residential or work permits, and 14 days' quarantine on all people entering.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-poland-foreigners-idUSKBN21031F|title=Poland to close borders to foreigners, quarantine returnees|newspaper=Reuters|date=March 13, 2020|via=www.reuters.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.pl/web/koronawirus/zamykamy-granice-przed-koronawirusem|title=Zamykamy granice przed koronawirusem|date=2020-03-13|via =www.Gov.pl}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.pl/web/koronawirus/pytania-i-odpowiedzi|title=Najcz\u0119\u015bciej zadawane pytania|via =www.Gov.pl}}</ref>\n**{{flag|Romania}}: Effective March 22, 2020 Romania banned foreign citizens from entering the country with the exception of official residents or those who are transiting the country.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.romania-insider.com/coronavirus-romania-borders-malls-closed|title=Coronavirus in Romania: Country closes borders for foreign citizens, malls close, people's movement and religious service restricted|website=Romania Insider|language=en|access-date=2020-03-25}}</ref>\n**{{flag|Slovakia}}: Closed its borders to all non-residents on March 13.<ref name=\"slovakia.1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-03-12/slovakia-closes-borders-for-non-residents-to-fight-coronavirus |title=Slovakia Closes Borders for Non-Residents to Fight Coronavirus |publisher=Bloomberg |date=2020-03-12 |accessdate=2020-04-08}}</ref>  Closed all three international airports and require all residents returning from abroad to 14 days quarantine in government designated quarantine facility.<ref name=\"slovakia.1\" />  Violators may be fined up to 1659 EUR.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uvzsr.sk/index.php?view=article&id=4087|title=COVID-19: \u00dastredn\u00fd kr\u00edzov\u00fd \u0161t\u00e1b zav\u00e1dza \u010fal\u0161ie opatrenia, zatvoria sa \u0161koly i letisk\u00e1, karant\u00e9na plat\u00ed pre v\u0161etk\u00fdch, ktor\u00ed sa vr\u00e1tia zo zahrani\u010dia |website=www.uvzsr.sk}}</ref>\n**{{flag|Spain}}: Closed borders to non-residents on March 17.<ref>{{cite web |title=Spain closes its borders to contain spread of coronavirus |url=https://english.elpais.com/society/2020-03-16/spain-closes-its-borders-to-contain-coronavirus.html |website=EL PA\u00cdS |accessdate=3 April 2020 |language=en |date=16 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n*{{flag|Albania}}: Closed borders on March 15 and all commercial flights on March 29.Therefore, travel between Albania and Montenegro, Kosovo, North Macedonia, and Greece is prohibited, unless for the transportation of goods.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.garda.com/crisis24/news-alerts/327276/albania-all-commercial-flights-suspended-from-march-29-due-to-covid-19-update-5|title=Albania: All commercial flights suspended from March 29 due to COVID-19 /update 5|last=|first=|date=|website=|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Moldova}}: Closed its airspace and terrestrial borders for all foreigners, except for diplomats and permanent residents, effective from 00:00 (UTC+02:00) March 17, 2020.<ref>[https://tass.ru/obschestvo/7984033 \u041c\u043e\u043b\u0434\u0430\u0432\u0438\u044f \u0437\u0430\u043a\u0440\u044b\u0432\u0430\u0435\u0442 \u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0446\u0443 \u0438\u0437-\u0437\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 \u0441 17 \u043c\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430]. tass.ru (15 March 2020)</ref>\n*{{flag|North Macedonia}}: Closed its borders on March 17.<ref>{{cite web |title=North Macedonia orders closure of all borders, Skopje airport |url=https://seenews.com/news/north-macedonia-orders-closure-of-all-borders-skopje-airport-691050 |website=seenews.com |accessdate=14 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Norway}}: Effective March 16, 2020, closed airports temporarily. Foreigners are turned away, and exemptions are made for Norwegians returning from abroad, and for goods.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-health-coronavirus-norway-airport-idUKKBN2110Z0|title=Norway to close ports, airports from Monday to stop coronavirus - PM|date=2020-03-14|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-03-15|language=en}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Russia}}: Borders closed to foreigners with some exceptions, effective March 18 and until May 1.<ref name=\"indepa9405131\">{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/coronavirus-russia-border-close-flights-when-residents-latest-a9405131.html|title=Russia closes borders until May amid coronavirus pandemic|date=March 16, 2020|website=The Independent}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Serbia}}: Closed its borders on March 16.<ref>{{cite web |title=Serbia closes its borders to foreigners over coronavirus |url=https://www.euractiv.com/section/justice-home-affairs/news/serbia-closes-its-borders-to-foreigners-over-coronavirus/ |website=www.euractiv.com |accessdate=3 April 2020 |date=16 March 2020}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Switzerland}}: Borders closed to foreigners, starting 17 March 2020.\n*{{flag|Turkey}}: Effective March 28, Turkey is suspending all international flights to and from Turkey, amid [[COVID-19]] outbreak. Turkey also closed its borders with all its neighbours.<ref name=\"aa1782602\" /><ref name=\"aa1770793\" />\n*{{flag|Ukraine}}: Starting March 15, Ukraine has closed its border for foreigners for two weeks. Returning Ukrainian citizens will be required to submit to health observation procedures.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://112.international/ukraine-top-news/ukraine-closing-border-for-foreigners-for-two-weeks-49475.html|title=Ukraine closing border for foreigners for two weeks|website=112.international}}</ref> Effective March 17, Ukraine is suspending all commercial passenger services, including flights, trains and passenger buses, to and from Ukraine for a period of two weeks.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ua.usembassy.gov/covid-19-information/|title=COVID-19 Information|date=March 13, 2020|website=U.S. Embassy in Ukraine}}</ref>\n\n===Oceania===\n* {{flag|Australia}}: Borders closed to all non-citizens or permanent residents from 21:00 March 20.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-03-19/coronavirus-non-resident-travel-ban-australia/12071640|title=Australia blocks arrival of all non-residents in expanded coronavirus travel ban|accessdate=March 19, 2020}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Marshall Islands}}: Passengers are not allowed to enter Marshall Isl. until 5 May 2020.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/tr/country/mh/ | title=Travel restrictions of Marshall Islands: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n* {{flag|New Caledonia}}: Passengers except parents of a French minor and spouses of a national of France are not allowed to enter New Caledonia. Flights to New Caledonia are suspended until 31 May 2020.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3605 | title=Travel restrictions of Vanuatu: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n* {{flag|New Zealand}}: Borders closed to all non-citizens or permanent residents (except for spouses or dependent children under 24 travelling with their New Zealand citizen or permanent resident spouse or parent) including the previously exempt Pacific Islands or temporary visa holders (such as students) from 23:59 March 19.<ref>{{cite web |title=Travelling to New Zealand |url=https://www.mfat.govt.nz/en/countries-and-regions/europe/united-kingdom/new-zealand-high-commission/living-in-the-uk/covid-19-coronavirus/ |website=New Zealand Ministry of Foreign Affairs and Trade |accessdate=17 April 2020 |language=English |date=9 April 2020 |quote=Immediate family members cannot travel by themselves. They must travel with the New Zealand citizen or resident family member on the same flight to New Zealand.}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.rnz.co.nz/news/national/412162/nz-to-close-its-borders-to-anyone-not-a-citizen-or-permanent-resident-pm-confirms|title=NZ to close its borders to anyone not a citizen or permanent resident., PM confirms|accessdate=March 19, 2020}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Fiji}}: Borders closed to all non-citizens.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.itij.com/latest/news/fiji-airways-suspends-95-cent-its-international-flights|title=Fiji closes borders|accessdate=March 22, 2020}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Tuvalu}}: Tuvalu's borders are closed.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/tr/country/tv/ | title=Travel restrictions of Tuvalu: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Vanuatu}}: Vanuatu ports of entry are closed from 20 March 2020.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/tr/country/vu/ | title=Travel restrictions of Vanuatu: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n\n==Countries and territories implementing global quarantine measures ==\n* {{flag|Australia}}: The Australian Government has announced that any person \u2013 regardless of citizenship or residency status \u2013 travelling to Australia from any international destination will be required to undergo a compulsory 14-day quarantine, beginning from their date of arrival. The regulations, effective from March 16, 2020, also ban cruise ships arriving from international waters from docking at any Australian port.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Wright |first1=Shane |title=PM introduces strict travel restrictions for all arrivals |url=https://www.smh.com.au/national/pm-introduces-strict-travel-restrictions-for-all-arrivals-20200315-p54a8q.html |work=The Sydney Morning Herald |date=15 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Benin}}: 14-day quarantine.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\" />\n*{{flag|Canada}}: Effective midnight March 25, 2020, the Canadian government announced an Emergency Order under the ''[[Quarantine Act, 2005|Quarantine Act]]'' that requires any person entering Canada by air, sea or land to self-isolate for 14 days whether or not they have symptoms of COVID-19.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.canada.ca/en/public-health/news/2020/03/new-order-makes-self-isolation-mandatory-for-individuals-entering-canada.html|title=New Order Makes Self-Isolation Mandatory for Individuals Entering Canada|date=March 25, 2020|website=Government of Canada}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Chile}}: Will not permit cruise ships to dock as of March 15. Travellers who have been to countries of concern are subject to examination or quarantine upon arrival.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cl.usembassy.gov/covid-19-information/|title=COVID-19 in Chile: Information for American Citizens|date=March 5, 2020|website=U.S. Embassy in Chile}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Ethiopia}}: Mandatory 14-day quarantine at the traveller's expense.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\" />\n* {{flag|Fiji}}: After the lockdown of [[Lautoka]] on 20 March 2020, no person regardless of citizenship is allowed to leave the confines of the city.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fbcnews.com.fj/news/covid-19/pm-no-exceptions-to-leave-lautoka-during-lockdown/|title=No exceptions to leave Lautoka|date=March 22, 2020|website=FBC}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Bailiwick of Guernsey|name=Guernsey}}: Imposed a requirement on all persons arriving in the Bailiwick from anywhere in the world (including Jersey and the UK) to self-isolate for 14 days on arrival. This is a legal requirement, and failure to comply is a criminal offence.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gov.gg/CHttpHandler.ashx?id=124043&p=0 |title= Imposition of a requirement to self-isolate by the Medical Officer of Health under the Emergency Powers (Coronavirus) (Bailiwick of Guernsey) Regulations, 2020 |date=19 March 2020 |website= www.gov.gg |access-date= 20 March 2020}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Hong Kong}}: Effective 19 March 2020, all persons arriving in Hong Kong who have been to Mainland China or any overseas countries/territories (excluding [[Macao]] and [[Taiwan]]) in the past 14 days, regardless of whether they are Hong Kong residents, are subject to compulsory quarantine.<ref>{{cite web |title=COVID-19 Thematic Website - Together, We Fight the Virus - Inbound Travel |url=https://www.coronavirus.gov.hk/eng/inbound-travel.html |publisher=Hong Kong SAR Government |accessdate=19 March 2020}}</ref> Effective 25 March 2020, all persons arriving in Hong Kong, regardless of whether they are Hong Kong residents, are subject to compulsory quarantine.<ref>{{cite web |title=HK to turn away many non-residents for 14 days |url=https://news.rthk.hk/rthk/en/component/k2/1516270-20200323.htm |publisher=RTHK |accessdate=23 March 2020}}</ref> \n* {{flag|Israel}}: From March 9, Israel instituted a blanket 14-day quarantine on all visitors and returning citizens.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.haaretz.com/israel-news/.premium-israeli-with-coronavirus-in-severe-condition-israel-may-quarantine-some-u-s-arrivals-1.8638322|title=Israel Extends Coronavirus Quarantine Orders to All Arrivals, 42 Cases Confirmed |date=2020-03-09|last=|first=|website=Haaretz|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-09}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Jersey}}: From Friday 20 March, all travellers arriving in Jersey must now self-isolate for 14 days. This includes the UK, Guernsey, Europe and the rest of the world.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.je/Health/Coronavirus/Pages/CoronavirusTravelAdvice.aspx |title=Travel advice for coronavirus (COVID-19) |publisher=Gov.je |date= |accessdate=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Malta}}: Tourists entering Malta from any country from 13:30 on March 13, 2020 onwards must spend 14 days in mandatory quarantine, which 14 days start from the last day that they were in any of these countries. This is enforceable by law. Failure to observe this obligation will result in fines of \u20ac1,000 for each time it is breached.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.visitmalta.com/en/Covid-19|title=Visitmalta - The official tourism website for Malta, Gozo and Comino.|website=www.visitmalta.com}}</ref>\n* {{flag|New Zealand}}: beginning 15 March 2020, any person entering New Zealand from overseas, including New Zealand citizens, will be required to self-isolate for 14 days following entry, except for those travelling from the Pacific Islands unless they are displaying symptoms. All cruise ships have been banned until 30 June 2020.<ref>{{cite news|title=Everyone entering New Zealand will be required to isolate, cruise ships banned|url=https://www.tvnz.co.nz/one-news/new-zealand/covid-19-everyone-entering-new-zealand-required-isolate-cruise-ships-banned|accessdate=15 March 2020}}</ref> Beginning 23:59 19 March 2020, New Zealand refused entry to non-citizens or permanent residents (with limited exceptions).<ref>{{cite news|title=NZ to close its borders to anyone not a citizen or permanent resident., PM confirms|url=https://www.rnz.co.nz/news/national/412162/live-nz-to-close-its-borders-to-anyone-not-a-citizen-or-permanent-resident-pm-confirms|accessdate=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Singapore}}: Effective 20 March 2020, all arrivals from abroad will be issued Stay-Home Notices lasting 14 days.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Wong |first1=Lester |last2=Lim |first2=Min Zhang|title=Coronavirus: Record 47 new cases in S'pore; 14-day stay-home notice will apply to all returning residents and short-term visitors |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/covid-19-all-time-high-of-47-new-cases-in-singapore-14-day-stay-home-notice-will-now-apply |website=The Straits Times |accessdate=18 March 2020 |date=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n* {{flag|South Korea}}: Effective April 1, 2020, all passengers are subject to mandatory self-quarantine for 14 days. This does not apply to airline crew.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3602 | title=Korea (Rep.) - restriction update 01.04.2020 02:52 UTC: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n\n==Non-global restrictions==\nMany countries have implemented measures that affect citizens of, or recent travellers to, a particular country or set of countries. Many of these countries later expanded their restrictions, with some later implementing global restrictions that may be listed above.\n\n* {{flag|Antigua and Barbuda}}: Visitors who have travelled through Austria, Belgium, Bulgaria, Canada, China (People's Rep.), Croatia, Cyprus, Czechia, Denmark, Estonia, Finland, France, Germany, Greece, Hungary, Iceland, Iran, Ireland (Rep.), Italy, Korea (Rep.), Latvia, Liechtenstein, Lithuania, Luxembourg, Malta, Netherlands, Norway, Poland, Portugal, Romania, Singapore, Slovakia, Slovenia, Spain, Sweden, Switzerland, USA or United Kingdom in the past 28 days are not allowed to enter or transit Antigua and Barbuda.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\" /> Banned arrivals from Japan.<ref name=\":0\" />\n* {{flag|Bahrain}}: Visa on arrival has been suspended. This does not apply to passengers with a diplomatic, an official, a service or UN passport. Passengers who have been in Austria, Belgium, China (People's Rep.), Czechia, Denmark, Estonia, Finland, France, Germany, Greece, Hungary, Iceland, Iran, Iraq, Korea (Rep.), Latvia, Liechtenstein, Lithuania, Luxembourg, Malta, Netherlands, Norway, Poland, Portugal, Slovakia, Slovenia, Spain, Sweden, Switzerland, United Kingdom and USA in the past 14 days are not allowed to transit and enter Bahrain. Passengers who have been in Hong Kong (SAR China), Italy, Japan, Lebanon, Malaysia, Singapore or Thailand in the past 14 days must have a valid visa prior to arrival.<ref name=\"3rKyw\">{{cite web|url=https://www.iatatravelcentre.com/international-travel-document-news/1580226297.htm |title=CORONAVIRUS OUTBREAK - UPDATE |publisher=Iatatravelcentre.com |date= |accessdate=2020-04-19}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Botswana}}: Visitors from Austria, Belgium, China (People's Rep.), Denmark, France, Germany, India, Iran, Italy, Japan, Korea (Rep.), Netherlands, Norway, Spain, Sweden, Switzerland, USA or United Kingdom are not allowed to enter or transit Botswana.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\" />\n* {{flag|Bulgaria}}: A temporary ban on entry imposed on all persons arriving from Italy, Spain, France, the United Kingdom, Germany, the Netherlands, Switzerland, Austria, Belgium, Iceland, Liechtenstein, Luxembourg and non-EU/Schengen countries. Visitors from some countries can transit through Bulgaria to return home.<ref>{{cite web |title=ORDER No \u0420\u0414-01-183 of 6 April 2020 |url=https://www.mfa.bg/upload/51859/MH-01-183_ENG%20(1).docx |publisher=Ministry of Health |accessdate=12 April 2020}}</ref> \n* {{flag|Cambodia}}: Visitors from France, Germany, Iran, Italy, Spain or USA are not allowed to enter Cambodia.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\" /> Visitors from Japan denied entry.<ref name=\":0\" />\n* {{flag|Gabon}}: Visitors who have travelled through Austria, Belgium, Bulgaria, China (People's Rep.), Croatia, Cyprus, Czechia, Denmark, Estonia, Finland, France, Germany, Greece, Hungary, Italy, Ireland (Rep.), Japan, Korea (Rep.), Latvia, Liechtenstein, Lithuania, Luxembourg, Malta, Netherlands, Norway, Poland, Portugal, Romania, Spain, Slovakia, Slovenia, Sweden, Switzerland, USA or the United Kingdom in the past 14 days are not allowed to enter or transit Gabon.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\" /><ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=https://www.anzen.mofa.go.jp/covid19/pdfhistory_world.html|title=\u65b0\u578b\u30b3\u30ed\u30ca\u30a6\u30a4\u30eb\u30b9\uff08\u65e5\u672c\u304b\u3089\u306e\u6e21\u822a\u8005\u30fb\u65e5\u672c\u4eba\u306b\u5bfe\u3059\u308b\u5404\u56fd\u30fb\u5730\u57df\u306e\u5165\u56fd\u5236\u9650\u63aa\u7f6e\u53ca\u3073\u5165\u56fd\u5f8c\u306e\u884c\u52d5\u5236\u9650\uff09|last=\u5916\u52d9\u7701|first=|date=|website=\u5916\u52d9\u7701 \u6d77\u5916\u5b89\u5168\u30db\u30fc\u30e0\u30da\u30fc\u30b8|language=ja|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Germany}}: Effective March 16, 2020 Germany has partially closed its borders with France, Austria, Denmark, Luxembourg, and Switzerland. However, goods will continue to flow between the countries to curb panic-buying.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-51897069|title=Germany to impose border controls over coronavirus|date=March 15, 2020|via=BBC News}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Greece}}: Initially suspended all passenger flights to and from Italy on March 14, excluding cargo and sanitary ones.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-greece-death/greece-reports-two-more-coronavirus-fatalities-suspends-all-flights-to-italy-idUSKBN2110H1|title=Greece reports two more coronavirus fatalities, bans all flights to Italy|date=March 14, 2020|agency=Reuters}}</ref> On March 16 Greece closed its borders with Albania and North Macedonia, only permitting the transportation of goods and the entry of Greek nationals and permanent residents, suspended ferry services to and from Italy and air links to Spain and prohibited all cruise ships and sailboats docking in Greek ports.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.news247.gr/politiki/koronoios-ektakta-metra-kleinoyn-ta-synora-me-alvania-kai-v-makedonia-tilefonima-mitsotaki-se-ieronymo.7602425.html|title=\u0395\u03ba\u03c4\u03b1\u03ba\u03c4\u03b1 \u03bc\u03ad\u03c4\u03c1\u03b1 - \u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u039a\u03bb\u03b5\u03af\u03bd\u03bf\u03c5\u03bd \u03c4\u03b1 \u03c3\u03cd\u03bd\u03bf\u03c1\u03b1 \u03bc\u03b5 \u0391\u03bb\u03b2\u03b1\u03bd\u03af\u03b1 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u0392. \u039c\u03b1\u03ba\u03b5\u03b4\u03bf\u03bd\u03af\u03b1 - \u03a0\u03b1\u03c1\u03ad\u03bc\u03b2\u03b1\u03c3\u03b7 \u039c\u03b7\u03c4\u03c3\u03bf\u03c4\u03ac\u03ba\u03b7 \u03b3\u03b9\u03b1 \u03c4\u03b9\u03c2 \u03b5\u03ba\u03ba\u03bb\u03b7\u03c3\u03af\u03b5\u03c2|website=www.news247.gr|language=el|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref> The same day it was announced that a 14-day home restriction will be mandatory for those who enter the country.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.news247.gr/koinonia/koronoios-kleinoyn-ta-emporika-katastimata-se-karantina-osoi-erchontai-apo-exoteriko.7603146.html|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u039a\u03bb\u03b5\u03af\u03bd\u03bf\u03c5\u03bd \u03c4\u03b1 \u03b5\u03bc\u03c0\u03bf\u03c1\u03b9\u03ba\u03ac \u03ba\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1\u03c3\u03c4\u03ae\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1 - \u03a3\u03b5 \u03ba\u03b1\u03c1\u03b1\u03bd\u03c4\u03af\u03bd\u03b1 \u03cc\u03c3\u03bf\u03b9 \u03ad\u03c1\u03c7\u03bf\u03bd\u03c4\u03b1\u03b9 \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc \u03b5\u03be\u03c9\u03c4\u03b5\u03c1\u03b9\u03ba\u03cc|website=www.news247.gr|language=el|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref> On 23 March Greece suspended all passenger flights from the UK as well as all sea, rail and road connections with Turkey, with an exception for Greek citizens and those who have residence permits, as well as trucks and ships that transport goods.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnn.gr/news/ellada/story/212372/koronoios-telos-apo-ta-mesanyxta-oi-ptiseis-apo-vretania-kai-toyrkia|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u03a4\u03ad\u03bb\u03bf\u03c2 \u03bf\u03b9 \u03c0\u03c4\u03ae\u03c3\u03b5\u03b9\u03c2 \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc \u0392\u03c1\u03b5\u03c4\u03b1\u03bd\u03af\u03b1 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u03a4\u03bf\u03c5\u03c1\u03ba\u03af\u03b1|last=Newsroom|date=2020-03-23|website=CNN.gr|language=el|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Japan}}: Passengers who have been in Albania, Andorra, Armenia, Australia, Austria, Bahrain, Belgium, Bolivia, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Brazil, Brunei Darussalam, Bulgaria, Canada, Chile, China (People's Rep.), Congo (Dem. Rep.), Cote d'Ivoire, Croatia, Cyprus, Czechia, Denmark, Dominica, Ecuador, Egypt, Estonia, Finland, France, Germany, Greece, Hong Kong (SAR China), Hungary, Iceland, Indonesia, Iran, Ireland, Israel, Italy, Korea (Rep.), Kosovo (Rep.), Latvia, Lithuania, Luxembourg, Macao (SAR China), Malaysia, Malta, Mauritius, Moldova (Rep.), Monaco, Morocco, Montenegro, New Zealand, North Macedonia, Panama, Philippines, Poland, Portugal, Romania, San Marino, Serbia, Singapore, Slovakia, Slovenia, Spain, Switzerland, Taiwan, Thailand, Turkey, USA, United Kingdom, Vatican or Viet Nam in the past 14 days are not allowed to enter.<ref name=\"3rKyw\" /><ref>{{cite web|author= |url=https://www.cathaypacific.com/cx/en_IL/travel-information/travel-preparation/travel-advisories/notice-regarding-travel-restrictions.html |title=Coronavirus (COVID-19) travel restrictions |publisher=Cathaypacific.com |date= |accessdate=2020-04-19}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Macau}}: Entry denied to all travellers except residents of mainland China, Hong Kong, Macau, or Taiwan.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://macaunews.mo/macau-prohibits-non-residents-from-entering-macau-with-the-exception-of-those-from-mainland-china-hong-kong-and-taiwan/|title=Macau Prohibits Non-Residents from Entering Macau with the exception of those from Mainland China, Hong Kong and Taiwan|website=Macau News |accessdate=19 March 2020}}</ref> Previously, restrictions were implemented for travellers coming from a smaller set of countries.\n* {{flag|Portugal}}: Closed its border with Spain to non-essential travel such as tourism on March 16.<ref>{{cite web |title=Portugal to close border with Spain to tourists |url=https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/portugal-to-close-border-with-spain-to-tourists/1762520 |website=Outlook India|accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Samoa}}: All travelers, including returning residents entering Samoa, must have a medical certificate issued by a registered medical practitioner issued within 3 days before their arrival into Samoa. Passengers who have transited through or have been in Australia, Austria, Bahrain, Belgium, Canada, China (People's Rep.), Czechia, Denmark, France, Germany, Greece, Hong Kong (SAR China), Iceland, Italy, Iran, Japan, Korea (Rep.), Kuwait, Luxembourg, Macao (SAR China), Malaysia, Netherlands, Norway, Qatar, Singapore, Spain, Sweden, Switzerland, Taiwan, Thailand, United Arab Emirates or USA are not allowed to enter Samoa.<ref name=\"3rKyw\" />\n* {{flag|South Korea}}: Effective April 13, 2020, citizens of countries that restricted visa-free travel for South Koreans will not be allowed visa-free travel in South Korea. <ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.immigration.go.kr/immigration_eng/1832/subview.do?enc=Zm5jdDF8QEB8JTJGYmJzJTJGaW1taWdyYXRpb25fZW5nJTJGMjI5JTJGNTIyNjQ5JTJGYXJ0Y2xWaWV3LmRvJTNGcGFzc3dvcmQlM0QlMjZyZ3NCZ25kZVN0ciUzRCUyNmJic0NsU2VxJTNEJTI2cmdzRW5kZGVTdHIlM0QlMjZpc1ZpZXdNaW5lJTNEZmFsc2UlMjZwYWdlJTNEMSUyNmJic09wZW5XcmRTZXElM0QlMjZzcmNoQ29sdW1uJTNEJTI2c3JjaFdyZCUzRCUyNg%3D%3D | title=Korea (Rep.) - Announcement on Suspension of Visas and Visa-Waiver}}</ref> Visas issued on or before 5 April are invalidated.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/4130 | title=Korea (Rep.) - restriction update 13.04.2020 03:56 UTC: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n*{{flag|United States}}: On January 31, 2020, the United States declared the virus a [[Public health emergency (United States)|public health emergency]]. Starting February 2, all inbound passengers who have been to Hubei in the previous 14 days will be put under quarantine for up to 14 days. American citizens who have travelled to the rest of mainland China will be allowed to continue their travel home if they are asymptomatic, but will be monitored by local health departments.<ref name=\"nbcnews1127856\" /> As of March 2, foreign nationals who have travelled to Iran within the past 14 days are denied permission to enter the US.<ref name=\"2020-03-02cnn\" /> American citizens and permanent residents returning to the United States who have travelled to Iran within the previous 14 days must enter through an approved airport.<ref name=\"2020-03-02cnn\" /><ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\" /> Suspended incoming travel from the [[Schengen area]] in Europe, beginning at 23:59 [[Eastern Time Zone|ET]] on March 13.<ref name=\"EUban\">{{cite web|url=https://www.whitehouse.gov/presidential-actions/proclamation-suspension-entry-immigrants-nonimmigrants-certain-additional-persons-pose-risk-transmitting-2019-novel-coronavirus/|title=Proclamation\u2014Suspension of Entry as Immigrants and Nonimmigrants of Certain Additional Persons Who Pose a Risk of Transmitting 2019 Novel Coronavirus|date=2020-03-11|website=The White House|first=Donald|last=Trump}}</ref> The official proclamation states that this restriction applies only to foreign nationals traveling to the United States, if they have been to a country within the [[Schengen area]] in the past 14 days. The ban does not apply to for example legal permanent residents and most immediate family members of U.S. citizens.<ref name=\"EUban\" /> Also, cargo and trading goods are not affected.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dw.com/en/coronavirus-latest-trump-suspends-travel-from-europes-schengen-countries/a-52731894|title=Coronavirus latest: Trump suspends travel from Europe's Schengen countries|website=Deutsche Welle|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-51846923|title=Trump halts travel from Europe to US|date=2020-03-12|work=BBC News|access-date=2020-03-12|language=en-GB}}</ref> On March 14, Trump administration extended the ban to include United Kingdom and Ireland.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foxnews.com/politics/trump-european-travel-ban-uk-ireland|title=Trump administration to extend European travel ban to include UK and Ireland|last=Shaw|first=Adam|date=2020-03-14|website=Fox News|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref> The restrictions will reportedly be in place for 30 days,<ref>{{Cite news|last=Specia|first=Megan|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/12/world/europe/trump-travel-ban-coronavirus.html|title=What You Need to Know About Trump's European Travel Ban|date=2020-03-12|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-03-15|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> however the official proclamation does not contain that time limit, stating; \"This proclamation shall remain in effect until terminated by the President.\"<ref name=\"EUban\" /> The move was criticised by EU leaders.<ref>{{cite news |title=EU condemns Trump travel ban from Europe as virus spreads |url=https://apnews.com/4552fd280d06cf83c63e4cc9b08fe5ce |work=Associated Press (AP) |date=12 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{Div col}}\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on aviation]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on cinema]]\n*[[2020 coronavirus pandemic on cruise ships]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on education]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on religion]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on politics]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on sports]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on television]]\n{{End div col}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|refs=\n\n<ref name=\"newsweek1484978\">{{cite web |url=https://www.newsweek.com/china-neighbors-close-borders-coronavirus-sars-1484978 |title=China's neighbors close borders as country's coronavirus cases surpass SARS |last=O'Connor |first=Tom |date=30 January 2020 |website=Newsweek |access-date=10 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200209125342/https://www.newsweek.com/china-neighbors-close-borders-coronavirus-sars-1484978 |archive-date=9 February 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"20200121reuters\">{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-pneumonia-northkorea/north-korea-to-suspend-foreign-tourism-over-coronavirus-fears-tour-company-idUSKBN1ZK1PK |title=North Korea suspends foreign tourism over coronavirus fears: tour companies |last=Smith |first=Josh |last2=Zhang |first2=Lusha |date=21 January 2020 |access-date=29 January 2020 |agency=Reuters}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"nbcnews1127856\">{{cite web |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/health/health-news/u-s-declares-public-health-emergency-over-coronavirus-n1127856 |title=U.S. declares public health emergency over coronavirus |publisher=NBC News |access-date=31 January 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200201084446/https://www.nbcnews.com/health/health-news/u-s-declares-public-health-emergency-over-coronavirus-n1127856 |archive-date=1 February 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"2020-03-02cnn\">{{cite web|url=https://edition.cnn.com/travel/article/coronavirus-travel-restrictions/index.html|title=Travelers will face new restrictions and cancellations as coronavirus cases grow in the US|first=Hollie|last=Silverman|website=CNN|access-date=2020-03-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302134536/https://edition.cnn.com/travel/article/coronavirus-travel-restrictions/index.html|archive-date=2020-03-02|url-status=live}} Updated 2nd March 2020</ref>\n\n}}\n\n{{COVID-19}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Travel restrictions related to the 2019-20 coronavirus pandemic}}\n[[Category:International responses to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on aviation]]\n[[Category:Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on tourism]]\n[[Category:Human migration]]\n", "name_user": "Rcheemalakonda", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eAsia", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Travel_restrictions_related_to_the_2019%E2%80%9320_coronavirus_pandemic"}
{"title_page": "Don't Start Now", "text_new": "{{pp-protected|small=yes}}\n{{About|the Dua Lipa song|the BoA song|Don't Start Now (BoA song)}}\n{{short description|2019 single by Dua Lipa}}\n{{Use British English|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox single\n| name         = Don't Start Now\n| type         = single\n| artist       = [[Dua Lipa]]\n| album        = [[Future Nostalgia (Dua Lipa album)|Future Nostalgia]]\n| cover        = Dua Lipa - Don't Start Now.png\n| alt          =\n| released     = {{Start date|df=yes|2019|10|31}}\n| format       =\n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n| recorded     =\n| genre        = [[Nu-disco]]<!-- Sourced in the \"Composition\" section. As per [[Template:Infobox song]]: \"This field should include the music genre(s) that best describes the song-->\n| length       = 3:03\n| label        = [[Warner Records|Warner]]\n| writer       = {{hlist|Dua Lipa|[[Caroline Ailin]]|[[Emily Warren]]|[[Ian Kirkpatrick (record producer)|Ian Kirkpatrick]]}}\n| producer     = Ian Kirkpatrick\n| prev_title   = [[Swan Song (song)|Swan Song]]\n| prev_year    = 2019\n| year         = 2019\n| next_title   = [[Physical (Dua Lipa song)|Physical]]\n| next_year    = 2020\n| misc         = {{External music video|{{YouTube|oygrmJFKYZY|\"Don't Start Now\"}}}}\n}}\n\"'''Don't Start Now'''\" is a song recorded by English singer [[Dua Lipa]] for her second studio album, ''[[Future Nostalgia (Dua Lipa album)|Future Nostalgia]]'' (2020). It was released by [[Warner Records]] as the album's [[lead single]] on 31 October 2019. Lipa wrote the track with [[Caroline Ailin]], [[Emily Warren]], and its producer [[Ian Kirkpatrick (record producer)|Ian Kirkpatrick]]. Inspired by music by the [[Bee Gees]] and [[Daft Punk]], \"Don't Start Now\" is a [[nu-disco]] song with several [[1980s in music|1980s]] and [[disco]] elements. It is built around a percolating [[Funk music|funk]] [[bassline]] and [[Accent (music)|accented]] disco strings. In the lyrics, Lipa addresses a former lover about moving on from their breakup. \n\n\"Don't Start Now\" received acclaim from music critics upon release, with many noting a significant growth in Lipa's sound and identity as a singer. The song was a commercial success worldwide, charting in the top 10 in over 40 different countries. It peaked at number two on both the [[UK Singles Chart]] and US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], surpassing 2017's \"[[New Rules]]\" to become Lipa's highest-charting single in the US. The music video for \"Don't Start Now\" was directed by [[Nabil Elderkin]], and shows Lipa passing through a basement nightclub and masked ball. To promote the single, the singer performed it on many television programmes, and at several awards shows, including the [[2019 MTV Europe Music Awards]] and [[American Music Awards of 2019|2019 American Music Awards]].\n\n==Background==\nLipa co-wrote \"Don't Start Now\" with the same team who wrote her 2017 single \"[[New Rules]]\": [[Caroline Ailin]], [[Emily Warren]] and [[Ian Kirkpatrick (record producer)|Ian Kirkpatrick]]. She said working with them again naturally made her choose it as ''[[Future Nostalgia (Dua Lipa album)|Future Nostalgia]]''{{'}}s [[lead single]] to \"close one chapter of my life and start another\" with a \"new sound\".<ref name=\"NME\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/dua-lipa-shares-snippet-of-new-track-dont-start-now-album-2559838|title=Dua Lipa shares new disco-tinged single 'Don't Start Now'|last=Skinner|first=Tom|website=[[NME]]|date=1 November 2019|accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref> \"Don't Start Now\" first came about after the [[Artists and repertoire|A&R]] head at Lipa's record label, Joe Kentish, challenged Kirkpatrick in late 2018 to produce another track for the singer following the success of \"New Rules\".<ref name=\"Billboard Interview\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/9350891/producer-ian-kirkpatrick-interview|title=Producer Ian Kirkpatrick on Chart Success During Quarantine: 'It's a Very Strange Duality'|last=LeDonne|first=Rob|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=6 April 2020|accessdate=14 April 2020|url-access=subscription}}</ref> The song was first composed at Ailin's home in [[Wyoming]].<ref name=\"SU\">{{cite web|url=https://www.songwriteruniverse.com/ian-kirkpatrick-songwriter-2020.htm|title=Ian Kirkpatrick Interview - Hit Songwriter and Producer|last=Kawashima|first=Dale|website=Songwriter Universe|date=20 February 2020|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Kirkpatrick recalls it being \"a back and forth\" between the [[1980s in music|1980s]] and [[disco]] sound that Lipa envisioned. Producer J Kash was involved during initial writing sessions.<ref name=\"Billboard Interview\"/>\n\nThe lyrics were written in January 2019 with a \"dance-around-the-room attitude\". Kirkpatrick included the use of a [[Cowbell (instrument)|cowbell]] in the first [[Demo (music)|demo]], based on phrasing in the chorus and inspired by music by [[Two Door Cinema Club]]. He produced the transition from the verse to the [[Drop (music)|drop]] using \"[[Can't Feel My Face]]\" by [[The Weeknd]] as an example.<ref name=\"Billboard Interview\"/> Although the [[bassline]] in \"Don't Start Now\" sounds live, Kirkpatrick created it with [[MIDI]]. It was influenced by similar basslines by the [[Bee Gees]] and [[Daft Punk]] that the producer listened to growing up. He described the production as a combination of his favourite disco and \"Euro-funk\" music.<ref name=\"SU\"/>\n\n==Composition==\n{{Listen\n | filename    = Dua Lipa Don't Start Now.ogg\n | pos         =\n | title       = \"Don't Start Now\"\n | description = A 16-second sample of the second verse where a [[rhythm guitar]] loop is added and Lipa sings with pauses between certain lyrics.<ref name=\"TSJ\"/>\n | format      = [[Ogg]]\n}}\n\"Don't Start Now\" is a [[nu-disco]]<ref name=\"Slant\">{{cite web|url=https://www.slantmagazine.com/music/review-dua-lipa-future-nostalgia-is-a-euphoric-escape-hatch-to-pops-past/|title=Review: Dua Lipa's Future Nostalgia Is a Euphoric Escape Hatch to Pop's Past|last=Cinquemani|first=Sal|website=[[Slant Magazine]]|date=25 March 2020|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Crack\">{{cite web|url=https://crackmagazine.net/article/album-reviews/dua-lipa-future-nostalgia/|title=Dua Lipa \u2013 'Future Nostalgia' review|last=Cragg|first=Michael|website=[[Crack Magazine]]|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"musicOMH\">{{cite web|url=https://www.musicomh.com/reviews/albums/dua-lipa-future-nostalgia|title=Dua Lipa \u2013 Future Nostalgia|last=Smith|first=Nick|website=[[musicOMH]]|date=27 March 2020|accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref> song with numerous 1980s and disco tropes,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2020/apr/05/dua-lipa-future-nostalgia-review|title=Dua Lipa: Future Nostalgia review \u2013 a dazzling dance through the decades|last=Empire|first=Kitty|author-link=Kitty Empire|website=[[The Observer]]|date=5 April 2020|accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref> and elements of [[Eurodance]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/amp/articles/business/chart-beat/8550118/dua-lipa-dont-start-now-five-burning-questions|title=Five Burning Questions: Billboard Staffers Discuss Dua Lipa's 'Don't Start Now' Hitting the Top 10|author=Billboard Staff|website=Billboard|date=4 February 2020|accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/dua-lipas-new-album-future-nostalgia-is-an-apocalypse-game-changer-and-the-best-album-of-2020-so-far|title=Dua Lipa's 'Future Nostalgia' Is an Apocalypse Game-changer\u2014and the Best Album of 2020 So Far|last=Fallon|first=Kevin|website=[[The Daily Beast]]|date=27 March 2020|accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref> The song is composed in [[Time signature|{{music|time|4|4}} time]] and the [[Key (music)|key]] of [[B minor]], with a [[tempo]] of 124 beats per minute. Constructed in [[verse-chorus form]], the verses have an Em\u2013Bm\u2013G\u2013D\u2013A [[chord progression]], while the chorus follows a Bm\u2013D\u2013Em7\u2013F{{music|sharp}}m7\u2013Gmaj7 sequence.<ref name=\"MN\">{{cite web|url=https://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/mtd.asp?ppn=MN0203029|title=Dua Lipa 'Don't Start Now' Sheet Music in B minor|publisher=Musicnotes.com|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> The track makes use of a percolating [[Funk music|funk]] bassline which interchanges with the beat.<ref name=\"SOS\">{{cite web|url=https://www.soundonsound.com/people/mix-review-march-2020|title=The Mix Review: March 2020|last=Senior|first=Mike|website=[[Sound on Sound]]|date=10 March 2020|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/music/music-reviews/dua-lipa-future-nostalgia-review/|title=Dua Lipa offers up high-octane pop bliss on Future Nostalgia|last=Johnston|first=Maura|author-link=Maura Johnston|website=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=26 March 2020|accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref> It also uses a cowbell in the middle of the chorus, [[laser weapon]] sound effects and clapping samples.<ref name=\"Billboard Interview\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vice.com/en_uk/article/vb5na4/dua-lipa-dont-start-now-listen-review|title=Dua Lipa's Disco Era 'Don't Start Now' Single Review|last1=Mokoena|first1=Tshepo|last2=Jones|first2=Daisy|last3=O'Neill|first3=Lauren|website=[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]]|date=1 November 2019|accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe song opens with a three-chord piano intro from the first part of the chorus and ends with a [[Phonographic record|vinyl]] hiss.<ref name=\"TSJ\">{{cite web|url=https://www.thesinglesjukebox.com/?p=28508|title=Dua Lipa \u2013 Don't Start Now|website=[[The Singles Jukebox]]|date=8 November 2019|accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"MN\"/><ref name=\"Vox\">{{cite podcast|url=https://podcasts.apple.com/gb/podcast/dua-lipas-disco-fever/id934552872?i=1000462452027|title=Switched on Pop: Dua Lipa's Disco Fever|website=[[Apple Music]]|publisher=[[Vox Media]]|date=10 February 2020|accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref> Lipa's vocals eschew modulation and build from a lower [[vocal register|register]] to a natural use of [[melisma]], spanning from [[A (musical note)|A<sub>3</sub>]] to [[D (musical note)|D<sub>5</sub>]].<ref name=\"MN\"/><ref name=\"Pitchfork\">{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/tracks/dua-lipa-dont-start-now/|title='Don't Start Now' by Dua Lipa Review|last=Strauss|first=Matthew|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|date=1 November 2019|accessdate=9 November 2019}}</ref> The track also builds with the addition of [[Accent (music)|accented]] disco strings,<ref name=\"The Guardian\">{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2019/nov/04/50-great-tracks-for-november-from-dua-lipa-destroyer-selena-gomez-and-more|title=50 great tracks for November from Dua Lipa, Destroyer, Selena Gomez and more|last1=Beaumont-Thomas|first1=Ben|last2=Snapes|first2=Laura|website=[[The Guardian]]|date=4 November 2019|accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/article/best-new-music-2019.html|title=Best New Music \u2014 December 6, 2019|author=Vulture Editors|website=[[Vulture.com]]|date=9 December 2019|accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref> and bursts of disco [[Synthesizer|synths]].<ref name=\"Pitchfork\"/><ref name=\"NME YE\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/features/the-50-best-songs-of-2019-2589036|title=The 50 best songs of 2019|website=NME|date=18 December 2019|accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref> It has a strong [[Kick drum|kick]] and [[bass drum|bass]] pattern that sparingly uses the [[Bass (sound)|low-end]]. After every fourth [[Bar (music)|measure]], a [[Fill (music)|fill]] is used, such as on the [[Snare drum|snare]]\u2013kick sequence that precedes the second verse.<ref name=\"SOS\"/> A [[rhythm guitar]] loop is added on the second verse, and a crowd noise on the second chorus.<ref name=\"TSJ\"/><ref name=\"Vox\"/> During the final chorus, chordal devices from the [[Breakdown (music)|breakdown]] reappear for [[Texture (music)|texture]] and Lipa sings in [[Call and response (music)|call and response]].<ref name=\"TSJ\"/><ref name=\"SOS\"/>\n\nThe lyrics of \"Don't Start Now\" are similar to Lipa's previous post-breakup song \"New Rules\". However, ''[[Stereogum]]'' notes that while \"New Rules\" dealt with the \"immediate aftermath\" of a breakup, \"Don't Start Now\" is \"a sequel of sorts, proof that those new rules really do work.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.stereogum.com/2063550/the-5-best-songs-of-the-week-311/franchises/the-5-best-songs-of-the-week/|title=Dua Lipa, HAIM & The Week's Best Songs: Listen|website=[[Stereogum]]|date=1 November 2019|accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref> It finds the singer celebrating her independence and using [[Bullet (typography)|bullet point]] instructions to directly address her former lover.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://time.com/5736115/best-songs-2019/|title=The 10 Best Songs of 2019|last1=Chow|first1=Andrew R.|last2=Bruner|first2=Raisa|website=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|date=28 November 2019|accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/dua-lipa-dont-start-now-new-song-904813/|title=Dua Lipa Returns With Disco Kiss-Off 'Don't Start Now'|last=Spanos|first=Brittany|website=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=1 November 2019|accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/amp/articles/columns/pop/9345029/dua-lipa-future-nostalgia-album-songs-ranking|title=Ranking All 11 Songs on Dua Lipa's 'Future Nostalgia': Critic's Take|last=Gracie|first=Bianca|website=Billboard|date=27 March 2020|accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref> According to Lipa, the lyrics are about \"moving on and not allowing anyone to get in the way of that.\"<ref name=\"NME\"/>\n\n==Release and promotion==\n[[File:Don't Start Now Times Square.jpeg|thumb|upright|[[Times Square]] billboards promoting the release of \"Don't Start Now\" in November 2019.<ref name=\"Telegrafi\">{{cite web|url=https://telegrafi.com/dua-lipa-vendoset-nga-youtube-ne-ekranet-gjigante-te-times-square/|title=Dua Lipa vendoset nga YouTube n\u00eb ekranet gjigante t\u00eb Times Square|language=Albanian|website=[[Telegrafi]]|date=5 November 2019|accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref>]]\n''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' first revealed the single's release date in an article about Lipa's management on 10 October 2019, but subsequently edited it to \"soon\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/music/news/tap-management-expands-hailee-steinfeld-lana-del-rey-1203362923/|title=TaP Management Expands With Hailee Steinfeld Signing, New West Coast Office|last=Herman|first=James Patrick|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=10 October 2019|accessdate=7 April 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191010225430/https://variety.com/2019/music/news/tap-management-expands-hailee-steinfeld-lana-del-rey-1203362923/|archivedate=10 October 2019}}</ref> Fans of the singer leaked the song's title and lyrics on [[Twitter]] on 14 October 2019.<ref name=\"video shoot\">{{cite web|url=https://www.thelineofbestfit.com/news/latest-news/dua-lipa-is-supposedly-releasing-new-single-dont-start-now-in-november|title=Dua Lipa is supposedly releasing new single 'Don't Start Now' in November|last=Kenneally|first=Cerys|website=[[The Line of Best Fit]]|date=15 October 2019|accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref>  Lipa shared two teaser videos on social media featuring snippets of the track on 22 and 23 October 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thelineofbestfit.com/news/latest-news/dua-lipa-drops-teaser-for-new-single-dont-start-now|title=Dua Lipa drops teaser for new single 'Don't Start Now'|last=Kenneally|first=Cerys|website=The Line of Best Fit|date=22 October 2019|accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thelineofbestfit.com/news/latest-news/dua-lipa-announces-release-date-for-new-single-dont-start-now|title=Dua Lipa announces release date for new single 'Don't Start Now'|last=Kenneally|first=Cerys|website=The Line of Best Fit|date=24 October 2019|accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref> The song was made available to pre-save on [[Spotify]] on 25 October 2019, in conjunction with a competition to win signed [[Instant film|polaroid]]s of the singer.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=DUALIPA|number=1187774578581487616|date=25 October 2019|title=I\u2019ve signed some polaroids we shot in New York last week... top lip not included \ud83d\ude29!! pre-save 'Don't Start Now' to get your hands on one xx \ud83d\udcf8\ud83d\udc98}}</ref> [[YouTube Music]] promoted the release on billboards in London and [[Times Square]].<ref name=\"Telegrafi\"/><ref>{{cite tweet|user=DUALIPA|number=1188498698642214912|date=27 October 2019|title=Too bloody excited!!!! Thank you @youtubemusic fammmm \u2764\ufe0f swipe for EXCITEMENT\ud83e\udd7a\u203c\ufe0f #DontStartNow}}</ref> The song was also promoted with its own lens filter on [[Snapchat]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hotpress.com/music/dua-lipa-drops-music-video-dont-start-now-22793267|title=Watch: Dua Lipa drops new single and music video, 'Don't Start Now'|last=Ransden|first=Brenna|website=[[Hot Press]]|date=1 November 2019|accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref> \n\n\"Don't Start Now\" premiered on 31 October 2019 at 13:00 [[Hawaii\u2013Aleutian Time Zone|HST]] (23:00 [[Coordinated Universal Time|UTC]]).<ref name=\"Premiere\">{{cite tweet|user=DUALIPA|number=1189821084230701058|date=31 October 2019|title=WORLD PREMIERE / CHECK UR TIMES / SET UR ALARMS / SEE U SOON \ud83d\udc9b\u203c\ufe0f\ud83d\udc9b\u203c\ufe0f\ud83d\udc9b\u203c\ufe0f}}</ref><ref name=\"EW Video\">{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/music/2019/10/31/dua-lipa-single-dont-start-now-listen/|title=Dua Lipa releases funky new single 'Don't Start Now' with music video sneak peek|last=Bucksbaum|first=Sydney|website=Entertainment Weekly|date=31 October 2019|accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref> ''[[The Radio 1 Breakfast Show]]'' exclusively played the song to an eight year-old fan of Lipa prior to its release.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://etcanada.com/news/533077/dua-lipa-releases-new-single-dont-start-now-after-previewing-for-8-year-old-superfan/|title=Dua Lipa Releases New Single 'Don't Start Now' After Previewing For 8-Year-Old Superfan|last=Furdyk|first=Brent|website=[[Entertainment Tonight Canada]]|date=31 October 2019|accessdate=8 April 2020}}</ref> On 15 November 2019, a [[vertical video]] and [[lyric video]] for the track were released on Spotify and [[YouTube]] respectively.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=DUALIPA|number=1195336578459164674|date=15 November 2019|title=Our @Spotify vertical video for Don't Start Now is up n running!! Check it out \ud83d\udc9b\u203c\ufe0f}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xjiYBGs0TUA|title=Dua Lipa - Don't Start Now (Official Lyric Video)|via=[[YouTube]]|publisher=Dua Lipa|date=15 November 2019|accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref> A live music video directed by Daniel Carberry was released on 10 January 2020, featuring Lipa performing an extended version of the song with a 19-piece live band in Los Angeles.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/dua-lipa-dont-start-now-live-video-935929/|title=Watch Dua Lipa Perform 'Don't Start Now' With 19-Piece Band|last=Zemler|first=Emily|website=Rolling Stone|date=10 January 2020|accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref> A remix [[Extended play|EP]] including remixes by [[Dom Dolla]], Purple Disco Machine, Zach Witness, [[Kungs]] and Pink Panda was released the same day.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.readdork.com/news/dua-lipa-dont-start-now-video-remix-ep|title=Dua Lipa has shared both a new remix EP, and a disco-infused live video for 'Don't Start Now'|website=[[Dork (magazine)|Dork]]|date=10 January 2020|accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref> On 24 January 2020, a remix by Kosovan DJ [[Regard (DJ)|Regard]] was released.<ref name = \"regard\"/> The Live in LA Remix was made available for [[Music download|digital download]] and [[Streaming media|streaming]] on 21 February 2020.<ref name=\"live\"/>\n\n==Critical reception==\n\"Don't Start Now\" received acclaim from music critics.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/markbeech/2020/03/26/why-dua-lipa-is-set-to-rival-ariana-grande-taylor-swift-with-future-nostalgia/#63dd85adb2ac|title=Why Dua Lipa Is Set To Rival Ariana Grande, Taylor Swift With 'Future Nostalgia'|last=Beech|first=Mark|website=[[Forbes]]|date=26 March 2020|accessdate=8 April 2020}}</ref> Brittany Spanos of ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' said the song took Lipa's sound to \"a higher level\" and that she \"finally finds her pop footing\", calling it \"the peak of pop catharsis\".<ref name=\"Rolling Stone\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/dua-lipa-dont-start-now-disco-song-you-need-to-know-907761/|title=Song You Need to Know: Dua Lipa, 'Don't Start Now'|last=Spanos|first=Brittany|website=Rolling Stone|date=4 November 2019|accessdate=9 November 2019}}</ref> Nick Malone of ''[[PopMatters]]'' wrote that the track displayed \"immeasurable\" growth in the singer's sound and identity, and that she was \"springing forth in full colour\" with sharper and more distinguishable vocals.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.popmatters.com/dua-lipa-future-nostalgia-2645576792.html|title=Dua Lipa: Future Nostalgia|last=Malone|first=Nick|website=[[PopMatters]]|date=27 March 2020|accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref> In the ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'', Mikael Wood commented that Lipa's \"throaty\" vocals grew more soulful on the \"delightfully rubbery\" song.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment-arts/music/story/2020-01-01/13-albums-2020-justin-bieber-selena-gomez-hasley|title=From Selena Gomez to Grimes, 13 artists with 2020 albums we can't wait to hear|last=Wood|first=Mikael|website=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=1 January 2020|accessdate=8 April 2020}}</ref> According to Conrad Duncan of ''[[Under the Radar (magazine)|Under the Radar]]'', the \"fantastically sleek\" track played to the singer's strengths.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.undertheradarmag.com/reviews/dua_lipa_future_nostalgia|title=Dua Lipa: Future Nostalgia (Warner) Review|last=Duncan|first=Conrad|website=[[Under the Radar (magazine)|Under the Radar]]|date=27 March 2020|accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref> ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]''{{'}}s Matthew Strauss wrote that the \"French bloghouse\" production suited Lipa and praised her for eschewing vocal modulation, saying \"her voice sounds stronger than ever\".<ref name=\"Pitchfork\"/>\n\nLaura Snapes of ''[[The Guardian]]'' wrote that Lipa distinguished herself from her contemporaries \"by eschewing the charts' predominant rap-influenced sound and going classic\", citing her vocals as the \"ritziest fixture\".<ref name=\"The Guardian\"/> Brad Garcia of ''[[Exclaim!]]'' meanwhile said \"it's more a homage than a blatant attempt to reinvent the wheel.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://exclaim.ca/music/article/dua_lipa-future_nostalgia|title=Dua Lipa Future Nostalgia|last=Garcia|first=Brad|website=[[Exclaim!]]|date=27 March 2020|accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref> ''[[musicOMH]]''{{'}}s Nick Smith described the song as a \"[[Moloko]]-esque nu-disco treasure\".<ref name=\"musicOMH\"/> Writing for ''[[Clash (magazine)|Clash]]'', Robin Murray called it \"a super-infectious disco burner\" with \"a [[Chic (band)|Chic]] flavour to the songwriting, given a chrome-plated 2019 overhaul,\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.clashmusic.com/news/dua-lipas-dont-start-now-is-a-super-infectious-disco-burner|title=Dua Lipa's 'Don't Start Now' Is A Super-Infectious Disco Burner|last=Murray|first=Robin|website=[[Clash (magazine)|Clash]]|date=1 November 2019|accessdate=9 November 2019}}</ref> while Yasmin Cowan said Lipa is \"ferocious in her execution\" and succeeds in \"putting her own feminist spin on the formulaic themes of break-ups\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.clashmusic.com/reviews/dua-lipa-future-nostalgia|title=Dua Lipa - Future Nostalgia|last=Cowan|first=Yasmin|website=Clash|date=26 March 2020|accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref> ''[[The Daily Telegraph]]''{{'}}s music critic [[Neil McCormick]] regarded it as \"a fantastic put-down of a needy ex\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/music/what-to-listen-to/dua-lipa-future-nostalgia-review-smashing-dancefloor-bangers/|title=Dua Lipa, Future Nostalgia, review: smashing dancefloor bangers from Britain's brightest pop star|last=McCormick|first=Neil|author-link=Neil McCormick|website=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|date=27 March 2020|accessdate=11 April 2020|url-access=subscription}}</ref>\n\nIn her review of ''Future Nostalgia'' for ''[[NME]]'', Rhian Daly deemed the song \"powerful pop perfection\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/dua-lipa-future-nostalgia-album-review-2633945|title=Dua Lipa \u2013 'Future Nostalgia' review|last=Daly|first=Rhian|website=NME|date=24 March 2020|accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref> [[AllMusic]]'s Neil Z. Yeung complimented Lipa's \"endless supply of confidence, charm, and cooler-than-you attitude\", and called the track an \"immediate [[earworm]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/future-nostalgia-mw0003359848|title=Future Nostalgia - Dua Lipa|last=Yeung|first=Neil Z.|publisher=[[AllMusic]]|date=2 April 2020|accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref> Marc Snetiker of ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' described it as a \"dance floor jawdropper\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/music-reviews/2020/01/31/friday-five-kesha-lil-wayne-demi-lovato/|title=EW Friday Five: Demi Lovato, Kesha, Lil Wayne, Porter Robinson, Dua Lipa|last1=Suskind|first1=Alex|last2=Nolfi|first2=Joey|last3=Jones|first3=Marcus|last4=Snetiker|first4=Marc|last5=Bucksbaum|first5=Sydney|website=Entertainment Weekly|date=31 January 2020|accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref> Chris Willman of ''Variety'' felt it brought \"a certain kind of deep groove and attitudinal buoyancy back onto the radio at a time we needed it most, which is anytime at all.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2020/music/news/dua-lipa-future-nostalgia-album-review-1203547968/|title=Dua Lipa's 'Future Nostalgia': Album Review|last=Willman|first=Chris|website=Variety|date=27 March 2020|accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref> In ''[[The New York Times]]'', [[Jon Caramanica]] said the track is \"effective but not overambitious\", arguing that Lipa sells its \"kiss-off sentiment with rhythm but not punch.\"<ref name=\"NY Times\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/11/01/arts/music/playlist-dua-lipa-ariana-grande-earl-sweatshirt.html|title=The Playlist: Dua Lipa's Disco Blast, and 13 More New Songs|last1=Pareles|first1=Jon|last2=Caramanica|first2=Jon|last3=Russonello|first3=Giovanni|website=[[The New York Times]]|date=1 November 2019|accessdate=1 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n\"Don't Start Now\" placed at number 17 in ''NME''{{'}}s 2019 year-end list.<ref name=\"NME YE\"/> It was nominated for Best British Song and Best Song in the World at the 2020 [[NME Awards|''NME'' Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/awards/8550933/nme-awards-2020-winners-list|title=2020 NME Awards Winners: The Complete List|website=Billboard|date=13 February 2020|accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Chart performance==\nIn November 2019, \"Don't Start Now\" debuted at number two on the [[UK Singles Chart]] with first-week sales of 49,334 units, making it Lipa's highest debut on the chart and seventh UK top 10 single.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.musicweek.com/analysis/read/charts-analysis-tones-and-i-holds-off-dua-lipa-at-singles-summit/078025|title=Charts analysis: Tones And I holds off Dua Lipa at singles summit|last=Jones|first=Alan|website=[[Music Week]]|date=8 November 2019|accessdate=12 April 2020|url-access=subscription}}</ref> It spent three consecutive weeks at number two, being kept from top spot by \"[[Dance Monkey]]\" by [[Tones and I]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.musicweek.com/analysis/read/charts-analysis-dua-lipa-and-billie-eilish-can-t-catch-tones-and-i/078187|title=Charts analysis: Dua Lipa and Billie Eilish can't catch Tones And I|last=Jones|first=Alan|website=Music Week|date=22 November 2019|accessdate=12 April 2020|url-access=subscription}}</ref> \"Don't Start Now\" has since charted for 23 weeks in the top 10, making it [[List of songs which have spent the most weeks on the UK Singles Chart|one of only eight songs to achieve this feat in the history of the chart]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/artist/48638/dua-lipa/|title=Dua Lipa full Official Chart History|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|accessdate=12 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.musicweek.com/analysis/read/charts-analysis-bank-holiday-weeknd-as-blinding-lights-is-no-1-for-seventh-week/079450|title=Charts Analysis: Bank holiday Weeknd as Blinding Lights is No.1 for seventh week|last=Masterson|first=James|website=Music Week|date=10 April 2020|accessdate=12 April 2020|url-access=subscription}}</ref> In January 2020, it was certified platinum by the [[British Phonographic Industry]] (BPI), which denotes track-equivalent sales of 600,000 units.<ref name=\"UKcertification\" /> On the [[Irish Singles Chart]], \"Don't Start Now\" debuted at number one, becoming Lipa's fourth chart-topper in Ireland, following 2017's \"New Rules\" and \"[[IDGAF (Dua Lipa song)|IDGAF]]\", and 2018's \"[[One Kiss (song)|One Kiss]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/dua-lipa-claims-fourth-number-1-on-the-official-irish-singles-chart-with-don-t-start-now-so-thankful-to-all-of-my-irish-fans-__27700/|title=Dua Lipa claims fourth Number 1 on the Official Irish Singles Chart with Dont Start Now: \"So thankful to all of my Irish fans!\"|last=White|first=Jack|publisher=Official Charts Company|date=8 November 2019|accessdate=12 April 2020}}</ref> It topped the chart for two consecutive weeks.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/dua-lipa-makes-it-two-weeks-at-the-top-of-the-official-irish-singles-chart-with-don-t-start-now__27746/|title=Dua Lipa makes it two weeks at the top of the Official Irish Singles Chart with Don't Start Now|last=White|first=Jack|publisher=Official Charts Company|date=15 November 2019|accessdate=12 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn Australia, \"Don't Start Now\" entered the [[ARIA Charts|ARIA Singles Chart]] at number eight, becoming Lipa's fifth single to reach the top 10 on the chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.noise11.com/news/australian-charts-tones-and-i-logs-up-15-weeks-at-no-1-20191110|title=Australian Charts: Tones and I Logs Up 15 Weeks At No 1|last=Ryan|first=Gavin|website=[[Noise11]]|date=10 November 2019|accessdate=13 April 2020}}</ref> In its sixth week, the song climbed to number two, tying \"New Rules\" as Lipa's highest-charting single in Australia.<ref name=\"ARIA 1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ariacharts.com.au/news/2019/tones-and-i-spends-20th-week-at-1|title=Tones And I Spends 20th Week At #1| publisher=[[ARIA Charts]]|date=14 December 2019|accessdate=13 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.noise11.com/news/australian-charts-tones-and-i-owns-no-1-for-20th-week-20191215|title=Australian Charts: Tones and I Owns No 1 for 20th Week|last=Ryan|first=Gavin|website=Noise11|date=15 December 2019|accessdate=13 April 2020}}</ref> \"Don't Start Now\" spent 10 non-consecutive weeks at number two, placing it in joint-second with \"[[Moves like Jagger]]\" by [[Maroon 5]] featuring [[Christina Aguilera]] for most weeks spent at number two without reaching number one.<ref name=\"Mediaweek\">{{cite web|url=https://www.mediaweek.com.au/aria-chart-american-rapper-lil-uzi-vert-at-1-dads-on-the-rampage/|title=ARIA Chart: American rapper Lil Uzi Vert at #1, Dads on the rampage|last=Manning|first=James|website=[[Mediaweek]]|date=16 March 2020|accessdate=13 April 2020}}</ref> The song has since spent 24 consecutive weeks in the top 10.<ref name=\"australianchart\"/> It received a double platinum certification from the [[Australian Recording Industry Association]] (ARIA) for sales of 140,000 units.<ref name=\"ARIA\"/>\n\n\"Don't Start Now\" debuted at number 30 on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] with a first-week tally of 14,000 downloads sold, 13.2 million streams and 10.2 million radio impressions.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8543290/dua-lipa-billboard-hot-100-dont-start-now|title=Dua Lipa Blasts Back Onto Billboard Hot 100 With 'Don't Start Now'|last=Zellner|first=Xander|website=Billboard|date=11 November 2019|accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref> In its 19th week on the chart, the song rose to number two, being held off the top spot by [[Roddy Ricch]]'s \"[[The Box (Roddy Ricch song)|The Box]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/hot-100/2020-03-21|title=The Hot 100 Chart|website=Billboard|accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/9335717/lil-uzi-vert-3-songs-hot-100|title=Roddy Ricch's 'The Box' Tops Hot 100 For 10th Week, Lil Uzi Vert Launches Three Songs in Top 10|last=Trust|first=Gary|website=Billboard|date=16 March 2020|accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref> It is Lipa's highest-charting single in the US and second to reach the top 10 after \"New Rules\".<ref name=\"Chart Beat\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/amp/articles/business/chart-beat/9352567/dua-lipas-top-5-billboard-200-debut-is-a-big-pop-moment-for-warner-records|title=Dua Lipa's Top 5 Billboard 200 Debut Is a Big Pop Moment for Warner Records|last=Caulfield|first=Keith|website=Billboard|date=6 April 2020|accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8549975/roddy-ricch-hot-100-number-one-third-week|title=Roddy Ricch's 'The Box' Tops Billboard Hot 100 for Fourth Week, Dua Lipa's 'Don't Start Now' Hits Top 10|last=Trust|first=Gary|website=Billboard|date=3 February 2020|accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref> \"Don't Start Now\" became Lipa's second chart-topper on the US [[Mainstream Top 40]] where it stayed at number one for six consecutive weeks.<ref name=\"Chart Beat\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/amp/articles/business/chart-beat/8551737/dua-lipa-tops-pop-songs-chart-dont-start-now|title=Dua Lipa's 'Don't Start Now' Hits No. 1 on Pop Songs Chart|last=Trust|first=Gary|website=Billboard|date=24 February 2020|accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref> It was also her seventh number one single on US [[Hot Dance Club Songs]] and first on the US [[Adult Top 40]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8547188/dua-lipa-scores-seventh-no-1-on-dance-club-songs-chart-with|title=Dua Lipa Scores Seventh No. 1 on Dance Club Songs Chart With 'Don't Start Now'|last=Murray|first=Gordon|website=Billboard|date=31 December 2019|accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/9357012/drake-toosie-slide-number-one-hot-100-debut|title=Drake Makes Historic Debut at No. 1 on Billboard Hot 100 With 'Toosie Slide'|last=Trust|first=Gary|website=Billboard|date=13 April 2020|accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref> On US [[Dance/Mix Show Airplay]], the song has led the chart for 16 consecutive weeks, [[Dance/Mix Show Airplay#Songs with the most weeks at number one|the second-longest stint at number one in the chart's history]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/hot-dance-airplay/2020-04-11|title=Dance/Mix Show Airplay Chart|website=Billboard|accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref> In March 2020, the track received a [[RIAA certification|platinum certification]] from the [[Recording Industry Association of America]] (RIAA) for track-equivalent sales of 1 million units.<ref name=\"riaa\"/> In Canada, it peaked at number three on the [[Canadian Hot 100]] and was certified double platinum by [[Music Canada]] for track-equivalent sales of 160,000 units.<ref name=\"canadianchart\"/><ref name=\"Canada Certification\"/>\n\n==Music video==\n===Development and release===\nThe music video for \"Don't Start Now\" was filmed on 14 October 2019 in [[Brooklyn]], New York.<ref name=\"video shoot\"/> It was directed by [[Nabil Elderkin]] and produced by Eric Brown.<ref name=\"Promonews\">{{cite web|url=https://www.promonews.tv/videos/2019/11/04/dua-lipa-dont-start-now-nabil/61667|title=Dua Lipa 'Don't Start Now' by Nabil|website=Promonews|date=4 November 2019|accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref> Lipa previously worked with Elderkin during her 2019 campaign for [[Yves Saint Laurent (brand)|Yves Saint Laurent]]'s Libre fragrance.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://vmagazine.com/article/dua-lipa-is-the-face-of-ysl-beautes-latest-fragrance/|title=Dua Lipa Is the Face of YSL Beaut\u00e9's Latest Fragrance|last=Harrison|first=Morgan|website=[[V (American magazine)|V]]|date=4 June 2019|accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vogue.com.au/beauty/news/dua-lipa-on-fashion-the-future-and-her-foray-into-fragrance/news-story/94e284ebaf6e6ed3e826ee89bd5a9956|title=Dua Lipa on fashion, the future and her foray into fragrance|last=Rippon|first=Remy|website=[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]|date=17 October 2019|accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref> Elderkin found inspiration for the [[Film treatment|treatment]] by skating around London while listening to the song. He used darker lighting and moods in a balance he felt complimented \"Don't Start Now\". Various concepts and edits were explored before Lipa and her management signed off the final cut. Lipa decided at the last minute to include the final scene at the start of the video.<ref name=\"The Face\">{{cite web|url=https://theface.com/music/dua-lipa-nabil-music-video-dont-start-now-bts|title=Dua Disco: behind the scenes of the 'Don't Start Now' video|last=Francombe|first=Amy|website=[[The Face (magazine)|The Face]]|date=6 November 2019|accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nLipa first shared an image from the music video on social media on 25 October 2019.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=DUALIPA|number=1187694465881952256|date=25 October 2019|title=7 Days #DontStartNow}}</ref> A [[Teaser campaign|teaser trailer]] was released on YouTube on 31 October 2019.<ref name=\"EW Video\"/> The music video premiered on YouTube the following day at 06:00 [[Pacific Time Zone|PT]] (13:00 UTC).<ref name=\"Premiere\"/>\n\n===Synopsis and reception===\n[[File:Dua Lipa - Don't Start Now music video screenshot.png|thumb|250px|right|alt=Dua Lipa dancing in a crowded nightclub.|A [[high-angle shot]] of the nightclub scene in which neon colour schemes are used.<ref name=\"The Face\"/>]]\nThe video opens with Lipa leaving a nightclub and throwing a [[point-of-view shot]] camera onto a sidewalk. The clip briefly blacks out before rewinding to a scene from five hours earlier.<ref name=\"V magazine\">{{cite web|url=https://vmagazine.com/article/dua-lipa-dont-start-now-music-video/|title=Dua Lipa Dances the Night Away in New 'Don't Start Now' Music Video|last=Kelly|first=Dylan|website=V|date=1 November 2019|accessdate=18 April 2020}}</ref> In this scene, Lipa enters a pub and removes her [[Raf Simons]] orange jacket to perform on stage in a [[Versace]] yellow bra top and [[Marni (fashion house)|Marni]] jeans.<ref name=\"Vogue\">{{cite web|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/dua-lipa-new-song-video-dont-start-now-disco|title=Watch Dua Lipa's New 'Don't Start Now' Video|last=Hahn|first=Rachel|website=Vogue|date=1 November 2019|accessdate=18 April 2020}}</ref> The video then cuts to a crowded nighclub where Lipa dances under a disco ball and spotlight.<ref name=\"V magazine\"/><ref name=\"Vogue\"/> In the next scene, Lipa dances at a [[19th century]]-themed [[masquerade ball]] before noticing eyes on paintings at the ball coming to life. She then runs down a staircase to return to the nightclub.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://dancingastronaut.com/2019/11/dua-lipa-immerses-viewers-in-party-fueled-journey-through-new-dont-start-now-music-video/|title=Dua Lipa immerses viewers in party-fueled journey through new 'Don't Start Now' music video|last=Sweeney|first=Farrell|website=[[Dancing Astronaut]]|date=1 November 2019|accessdate=19 April 2020}}</ref> Lipa is later shown washing her face in the nightclub's bathroom and strutting in its hallway. The video ends with a cumalitive montage of the evening's events.<ref name=\"V magazine\"/>\n\nAmy Francombe of ''[[The Face (magazine)|The Face]]'' said Elderkin's signature directing style \"shines through\" with the use of neon colour schemes and [[high-angle shot]]s.<ref name=\"The Face\"/> Brendan Wetmore of ''[[Paper (magazine)|Paper]]'' described the video as \"something straight out of the POV [[TikTok]] genre and put onto [[Vevo]].\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.papermag.com/dua-lipa-dont-start-now-2641185042.html|title=Dua Lipa Releases 'Don't Start Now' Video|last=Wetmore|first=Brendan|website=[[Paper (magazine)|Paper]]|date=1 November 2019|accessdate=18 April 2020}}</ref> In her review for ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]'', Rachel Hahn called it \"a fine showcase for Lipa's expert post-breakup style\" and said she looked \"carefree in the best way possible\".<ref name=\"Vogue\"/> Writing for ''[[V (magazine)|V]]'' magazine, Dylan Kelly felt it highlighted Lipa's \"free spirit and elated independence.\"<ref name=\"V magazine\"/> On the other hand, ''[[Nylon (magazine)|Nylon]]''{{'}}s Allison Stubblebine commented, \"Instead of enjoying herself in a sea of sweaty bodies like [[Harry Styles]] in '[[Lights Up]]', she's stressed out and should probably go home.\"<ref name=\"Nylon\">{{cite web|url=https://nylon.com/dua-lipa-dont-stop-now|title=Dua Lipa's 'Don't Stop Now' Video Finds Her In The Club|last=Stubblebine|first=Allison|website=[[Nylon (magazine)|Nylon]]|date=1 November 2019|accessdate=18 April 2020}}</ref> The music video has received over 230 million views on YouTube.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oygrmJFKYZY|title=Dua Lipa - New Love (Official Music Video)|via=YouTube|date=1 November 2019|accessdate=19 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Live performances==\nLipa gave her first live performance of \"Don't Start Now\" on 1 November 2019 on ''[[The Graham Norton Show]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertainment.ie/tv/tv-news/graham-norton-show-great-lineup-tonight-427819/|title='The Graham Norton Show' has a great lineup in store tonight|last=Flynn|first=Fiona|website=[[entertainment.ie]]|date=1 November 2019|accessdate=19 April 2020}}</ref> Lipa then performed the song at the [[2019 MTV Europe Music Awards]] on 3 November 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/watch-dua-lipa-give-dont-start-now-live-debut-mtv-emas-2564129|title=Watch Dua Lipa perform 'Don't Start Now' at the MTV EMAs 2019|last=Gwee|first=Karen|website=NME|date=4 November 2019|accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref> She wore a black leotard and was surrounded by a float of 40 dancers in yellow bodysuits during the [[Es Devlin]]-directed performance.<ref name=\"The Face\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/dua-lipa-dont-start-now-mtv-emas-907545/|title=Watch Dua Lipa Perform 'Don't Start Now' at MTV EMAs|last=Zemler|first=Emily|website=Rolling Stone|date=4 November 2019|accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref> The performance was acclaimed in the media.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aria.com.au/documents/ARIAChartsPressRelease191118.pdf|title=Tones and I Breaks the All-Time ARIA Singles Chart Record|publisher=ARIA Charts|format=PDF|accessdate=19 April 2020}}</ref> [[BBC News]] wrote, \"Fans who'd previously made fun of her stage presence were won over by the dance moves and staging.\"<ref name=\"BBC\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-52117012|title=Dua Lipa interview: How I released an album from lockdown|last=Savage|first=Mark|publisher=[[BBC News]]|date=2 April 2020|accessdate=19 April 2020}}</ref> Zoya Raza-Sheikh of ''Clash'' said, \"All it took was a few minutes for the singer to - yet again - prove a questioning audience wrong.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.clashmusic.com/features/dua-lipa-is-the-perfect-pop-star-for-these-times|title=Dua Lipa Is the Perfect Pop Star For These Times|last=Raza-Sheikh|first=Zoya|website=Clash|date=3 April 2020|accessdate=19 April 2020}}</ref> Evan Sawdey of ''PopMatters'' praised Lipa for \"nailing tight choreography and delivering a striking stage presence heretofore unseen.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.popmatters.com/dua-lipa-future-nostalgia-review-2645577176.html|title=Dua Lipa: Future Nostalgia (take 2)|last=Sawdey|first=Evan|website=PopMatters|date=31 March 2020|accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 10 November 2019, Lipa performed \"Don't Start Now\" on the [[The Voice of Germany (season 9)|ninth season]] finale of ''[[The Voice of Germany]]'' with contestant Freschta Akbarzada.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.prosieben.de/stars/the-voice-of-germany/finale-im-livestream-the-voice-of-germany-2019-106823|title=Finale im Livestream - 'The Voice of Germany' 2019|language=German|website=[[ProSieben]]|date=10 November 2019|accessdate=19 April 2020}}</ref> She also performed the song amid a festival of silver balloons at the [[American Music Awards of 2019|2019 American Music Awards]] on 24 November 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/dua-lipa-dont-start-now-2019-amas-916900/|title=Watch Dua Lipa Perform 'Don't Start Now' at the 2019 AMAs|last=Shaffer|first=Claire|website=Rolling Stone|date=24 November 2019|accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref> In Australia, Lipa performed the track at the [[ARIA Music Awards of 2019|2019 ARIA Music Awards]] on 27 November, and on breakfast television programme ''[[Sunrise (Australian TV program)|Sunrise]]'' the following day.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://graziamagazine.com/articles/dua-lipa-aria-awards-2019/|title=ARIA Awards 2019: Dua Lipa's Sartorial Nod To Cher Horowitz|last=Bailey|first=Jessica|website=[[Grazia]]|date=27 November 2019|accessdate=19 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://7news.com.au/sunrise/entertainment/dua-lipa-headlines-the-sunrise-summer-party-live-from-hamilton-island-c-581275|title=Dua Lipa headlines the Sunrise Summer Party live from Hamilton Island|website=[[Seven News]]|date=29 November 2019|accessdate=19 April 2020}}</ref> In Japan, Lipa performed \"Don't Start Now\" in an all-black Versace outfit at the [[2019 Mnet Asian Music Awards]] on 4 December 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nylon.com/dua-lipa-versace-2019-mnet-asian-music-awards|title=Dua Lipa Wears Versace To The 2019 Mnet Asian Music Awards|last=Harwood|first=Erika|website=Nylon|date=4 December 2019|accessdate=19 April 2020}}</ref> Her performance was preceded by a rendition of \"New Rules\" by South Korean singer [[Hwasa]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.republicworld.com/entertainment-news/music/dua-lipa-just-serenaded-the-k-pop-awards-in-style-read-on-how.html|title=Dua Lipa just serenaded the K-pop MAMA awards in style. How? Read on.|last=Bhandary|first=Shrishaila|website=[[Republic TV]]|date=5 December 2019|accessdate=19 April 2020}}</ref> On 17 December 2019, Lipa performed \"Don't Start Now\" on the [[The Voice (American season 17)|17th US season]] finale of ''[[The Voice (American TV series)|The Voice]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/the-voice-winner-season-17-1203446701/|title='The Voice' Winner: Season 17 Announces Winner|last=Nyren|first=Erin|website=Variety|date=17 December 2019|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> On 19 December 2019, Lipa performed the track with a [[string section]] on ''[[The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/dua-lipa-dont-start-now-tonight-show-929876/|title=Dua Lipa Performs Disco-Inspired 'Don't Start Now' on 'Tonight Show'|last=Shaffer|first=Claire|website=Rolling Stone|date=20 December 2019|accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref>  The next day the song was performed on the American morning television show ''[[Good Morning America]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.reddit.com/r/popheads/comments/edoazf/dua_lipa_performs_dont_start_now_live_on_good/|title=r/popheads - Dua Lipa performs Don't Start Now live on Good Morning America|website=reddit|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-03}}</ref> Furthermore, Lipa performed the song on [[Dick Clark's New Year's Rockin' Eve]] 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2020/01/video-dua-lipa-dick-clark-nye/|title=Dua Lipa performs \"Don't Start Now\" on Dick Clark's New Year's Rockin' Eve: Watch|date=1 January 2020|website=Consequence of Sound|accessdate=3 January 2020}}</ref> On 9 January, Lipa performed the song on ''[[The Ellen DeGeneres Show]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8547667/dua-lipa-performs-dont-start-now-ellen-video|title=Watch Dua Lipa's Fierce Performance of 'Don't Start Now' on 'Ellen'|website=www.billboard.com|date=9 January 2020|language=en|access-date=2020-02-17}}</ref> On 7 February, Lipa performed the song at the [[Sanremo Music Festival 2020|Sanremo Music Festival]] in Italy.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dailynewsgh.com/2020/02/07/dua-lipa-performs-dont-start-now-at-sanremo-music-festival-2020/|title=Dua Lipa Performs 'Don't Start Now' at SanRemo Music Festival 2020 {{!}} Daily News|last=Gringo|first=Alhaji|date=2020-02-07|website={{!}} Daily News|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-17}}</ref> On 30 March 2020, Lipa performed \"Don't Start Now\" by video conference call from her London apartment for ''[[The Late Late Show with James Corden]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/watch-dua-lipa-and-her-band-give-video-conference-performance-on-james-cordens-homefest-2638167\"|title=Watch Dua Lipa and her band give video conference performance on James Corden's 'HomeFest'|last=Daly|first=Rhian|website=NME|date=31 March 2020|accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Track